1
00:00:52,969 --> 00:00:56,322
- It's lucky it didn't reach the house. - Yeah.
- 这火没有烧到房子算是幸运的了 - 对啊

2
00:00:57,783 --> 00:00:59,333
You know,
你知道么

3
00:00:59,340 --> 00:01:03,186
there's gonna be a lot more jobs at
that factory in Milwaukee come June.
等到六月份Milwaukee（密尔沃基）的工厂来了，工作岗位就多了

4
00:01:05,126 --> 00:01:08,867
- I could put in a word. - You can't leave us, Henry.
- 我可以帮你走走关系 - 你不能留下我们，Henry

5
00:01:08,890 --> 00:01:10,922
She needs us both.
她需要我们俩

6
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:13,818
Can you stop being a momma's boy for one second?
你能不能先不当妈妈的宝贝？

7
00:01:15,467 --> 00:01:17,768
I'm not trying to hurt you, but Jesus,
我这不是伤害你的感情，可是，老天爷

8
00:01:17,792 --> 00:01:20,010
you got to live your own life sometime.
你也得自力更生一下吧

9
00:01:20,034 --> 00:01:22,614
That woman can take care of her own goddamn...
那女人完全可以照顾自己。。。oops

10
00:01:35,981 --> 00:01:37,907
Oh, good evening.
矮油，晚上好

11
00:01:37,930 --> 00:01:41,018
Brother has been killing brother since Cain and Abel,
从该隐和亚伯开始，兄弟之间就开始自相残杀

12
00:01:41,042 --> 00:01:43,417
yet even I didn't see that coming.
然而这对我还是出乎意料

13
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:47,022
I was as blind-sided as poor old Henry down there.
我就跟躺在那儿的可怜的Henry一样被蒙骗

14
00:01:47,045 --> 00:01:51,638
Apparently the authorities shared my naivet
而且显然有关部门也同样的天真

15
00:01:51,661 --> 00:01:55,021
In other words, they believed the young man's story
换句话说，他们相信这个凶手的说辞：

16
00:01:55,044 --> 00:01:58,085
that Henry fell, hit his head on a stone,
亨利跌倒了，他的头撞到了石头上

17
00:01:58,106 --> 00:02:01,438
and died of smoke asphyxiation.
死因是烟雾窒息

18
00:02:02,976 --> 00:02:05,994
On the other hand, if they hadn't believed him,
另一方面，如果有关部门不相信他

19
00:02:06,017 --> 00:02:10,473
Ed Gein would never have had the opportunity to commit those
Ed Gein就永远不会有机会招认那些

20
00:02:10,493 --> 00:02:15,371
heinous crimes for which he became most famous.
那些可以让他成名的凶残的罪行

21
00:02:15,395 --> 00:02:21,033
And we, of course, well... We wouldn't have our little movie, would we?
而我们，呵呵，也没法看到有关他的电影了不是么？

22
00:02:21,819 --> 00:02:26,797
希区柯克噔噔噔
Sync, corrected by icephoenix 
中字：三十    校对：小野

23
00:02:39,731 --> 00:02:41,343
Here he comes!

24
00:02:45,389 --> 00:02:47,575
This thing's going to be gigantic.
这部电影一定会成为大事件

25
00:02:47,598 --> 00:02:50,264
I wish I had 20% of the take.
我希望我能有百分之二十的镜头（应该不是这样翻译）

26
00:02:50,289 --> 00:02:53,244
Does tonight's incredible reaction surprise you, Mr. Hitchcock?
今晚这无与伦比的反响让你吃惊么，希区柯克先生？

27
00:02:53,267 --> 00:02:56,148
No, when I was planning North by Northwest
不吃惊。当我还在筹划《西北偏北》的时候

28
00:02:56,163 --> 00:02:59,950
I could already hear the screams and the laughter.
我已经能听到观众的尖叫声和笑声了

29
00:03:00,498 --> 00:03:04,198
Any questions, my dear? Pity.
有什么问题么，美人？（美人摇头）真遗憾

30
00:03:04,209 --> 00:03:07,914
Mr. Hitchcock, you've directed 46 motion pictures.
希区柯克先生，你已经执导了46部电影

31
00:03:07,937 --> 00:03:10,321
You're the most famous director in the history of the medium...
你已经成为电影史上最著名的导演了

32
00:03:10,339 --> 00:03:12,810
But you're sixty years old.
可是你已经60岁了

33
00:03:12,834 --> 00:03:15,023
Shouldn't you just quit while you're ahead?
为什么不趁你现在的成功而退出呢？

34
00:03:31,271 --> 00:03:35,748
Muhammad had the eyes of peeping Toms gouged out with arrows.
穆罕默德的眼睛就是因为偷窥被人用箭矢挖了出来

35
00:03:35,768 --> 00:03:38,791
That must have been rather painful.
那一定非常疼

36
00:03:38,803 --> 00:03:40,858
Talking of arrows,
说起箭

37
00:03:40,881 --> 00:03:45,963
did you read that little snippet from A.H. Weiler's review in The New York Times?
你看到纽约时报上A.H.Weiler写的短评么？

38
00:03:45,987 --> 00:03:49,822
He said he found the climax to be "overdrawn."
他说他觉得影片的高潮”太过了“

39
00:03:49,845 --> 00:03:53,535
Yes, well I doubt Mr. Weiler has had a climax in years.
我倒是怀疑他这几年没有过高潮

40
00:03:53,558 --> 00:03:57,820
"North by Northwest reminds us of Mr. Hitchcock's
“《西北偏北》让我们想起希区柯克早期的作品，

41
00:03:57,843 --> 00:04:01,474
earlier, more inventive spy thrillers."
那些更加有创意的间谍惊悚片。”

42
00:04:01,497 --> 00:04:04,010
And there is an accompanying list.
这还有个（新悬念大师）的名单

43
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:08,166
The "New Masters of Suspense."
新生代悬念大师

44
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:11,851
Why do they keep looking for new ones when they still have the original?
为什么明知原汁原味的还在他们还要找新人啊？

45
00:04:11,874 --> 00:04:14,666
Oh, don't be maudlin, you know how much it aggravates me.
矮油，别多愁善感了，你也知道这玩意儿多容易激怒我

46
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:16,559
Just stop reading them.
别读了

47
00:04:16,582 --> 00:04:18,440
You've been reading them for a week.
你已经看这些文章一个星期了

48
00:04:19,566 --> 00:04:21,045
Tell me, my dear,
说实话亲爱的

49
00:04:21,069 --> 00:04:23,466
do you think I'm too old?
你觉得我已经老了么？

50
00:04:25,285 --> 00:04:28,252
Yes, you're a true relic.
没错，你是个活化石

51
00:04:28,275 --> 00:04:31,425
And lest we forget, a notably corpulent one.
而且还是一个肥胖的活化石

52
00:04:32,468 --> 00:04:36,843
You always know precisely where to plunge the dagger, don't you?
你总是准确地知道人的痛处在哪儿，不是么？

53
00:04:36,866 --> 00:04:39,948
Right between the shoulder blades. I learned it from your pictures.
不就在一对肩胛骨之间么，这可是从你电影里学到的

54
00:04:39,972 --> 00:04:42,755
Where, may I ask, are you off to?
那么我能问一下，你现在要去哪儿？

55
00:04:42,778 --> 00:04:44,704
I'm going to have brunch with Whit
把你送到工作室后

56
00:04:44,727 --> 00:04:47,353
after I drop you off at the studio. Would you care to join us?
我就去和Whit吃早午餐。难道你也想来？

57
00:04:47,376 --> 00:04:50,162
We've just established that I'm far too corpulent
我们刚刚才说过我太胖了

58
00:04:50,163 --> 00:04:52,275
to be seen in broad daylight.
不宜出现在大白天

59
00:04:52,299 --> 00:04:55,064
Oh, you'll feel better when you find a new project.
矮油，当你发掘到新的项目你就会好起来的了

60
00:04:55,087 --> 00:04:57,730
Hasn't Peggy unearthed any decent books for you recently?
Peggy最近不是给你找了不少不错的书么？

61
00:04:57,753 --> 00:05:00,788
Yes, sleeping pills with dust jackets.
都是些书套包起来的安眠药

62
00:05:01,982 --> 00:05:04,911
So what do you think?
我怎么样？

63
00:05:05,849 --> 00:05:08,198
Very presentable.
见得了人

64
00:05:11,374 --> 00:05:13,781
Hurry up, dear, you're pruning.
快点吧，你在摆臭脸了

65
00:05:13,781 --> 00:05:14,781
（这一刻感觉《哈利波特》灵魂附体）

66
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:27,082
- Good Morning. - Ms. Hitchcock.
- 早上好！ - 希区柯克夫人

67
00:05:27,105 --> 00:05:28,796
Mr. Hitchcock.
希区柯克先生

68
00:05:28,819 --> 00:05:30,424
Sirs.
小狗们

69
00:05:38,384 --> 00:05:42,117
There's a project out there waiting for you, Hitch. I promise you.
希爱，你总会想到新的项目的。我敢打赌！

70
00:05:42,141 --> 00:05:45,474
- I hope so. Thank you, love. - Have a good day.
- 但愿如此。谢谢亲爱的。 - 祝你有好的一天

71
00:05:48,934 --> 00:05:53,290
I'm treading water, Peggy. I need something fresh, something different.
我如同走在水面上了现在。我需要新鲜的想法，新奇的想法！

72
00:05:53,314 --> 00:05:56,403
Without expensive stars to pretty it up.
而不是找一帮昂贵的明星来做个花枕头

73
00:05:56,427 --> 00:06:00,544
Fox is offering you The Diary of Anne Frank for the third time.
福克斯已经是第三次邀请你参与《安妮日记》了

74
00:06:00,567 --> 00:06:03,458
The audience would spend the entire picture waiting for Miss Frank
观众们难道会花一部电影的时间等着安妮

75
00:06:03,459 --> 00:06:06,280
to discover the corpse I'd hidden in the attic.
发现藏在阁楼的尸体么

76
00:06:06,301 --> 00:06:08,614
- Wouldn't you agree, Nuncio? - Si.
- 是吧，Nuncio？ - 对（意大利语）

77
00:06:08,638 --> 00:06:11,945
MGM wants you for the Ian Fleming book, Casino Royale.
MGM想让你考虑一下弗莱明的新书《皇家赌场》

78
00:06:11,969 --> 00:06:14,540
Cary Grant. Definitely your style.
加里・格兰特加盟，是你的风格

79
00:06:14,564 --> 00:06:18,431
Doesn't she know I just made that movie? It's called North by Northwest.
她不知道我才拍了部有他的电影么？叫《Xi Bei Pian Bei》

80
00:06:18,449 --> 00:06:21,279
"Style," my dear, is mere self-plagiarism.
而且所谓“风格”，亲爱的我告诉你，就是自我剽窃

81
00:06:21,302 --> 00:06:23,826
Oh, scusi!
对不起！

82
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:27,736
A nice, clean, nasty little piece of work. That's what I'm looking for.
漂亮、简洁、让人讨厌的小故事才是我们的目标

83
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:30,118
I shall see what I can find.
我看看我能找到什么

84
00:06:32,929 --> 00:06:34,816
- Serves you right. - Yeah.
- 你真是活该哈哈 - 对啊

85
00:06:35,614 --> 00:06:38,665
You know, Hitch always says that your private life
你知道么，老希总是说你活在你的私人生活

86
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:41,623
is in danger of being more entertaining than any of your plots.
总是比你演的剧情还要精彩的危险当中

87
00:06:41,647 --> 00:06:45,034
I'm surprised he let me have you for the whole afternoon.
我很惊喜你让我陪了你整个下午

88
00:06:45,057 --> 00:06:47,287
Especially looking so beautiful.
而且你还那么漂亮

89
00:06:47,309 --> 00:06:50,880
So tell me, what are you working on these days?
跟我说说，你最近在忙啥呢？

90
00:06:50,903 --> 00:06:53,289
Me? Oh, oh...
我么，嗯，

91
00:06:53,313 --> 00:06:55,685
I'm satisfied working in my garden.
我一直悉心打理我的花园

92
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:58,800
Oh! Well that's one lucky garden.
那可是一个幸运的花园

93
00:07:00,185 --> 00:07:05,140
All this relentless sycophancy is actually giving me indigestion.
您的这些不断的阿谀奉承我真是消化不了了

94
00:07:05,164 --> 00:07:07,806
What are you after?
我们开门见山吧？

95
00:07:07,829 --> 00:07:14,627
I was hoping you may be able to apply your considerable pruning skills to this.
我只是在想你能不能在这上面使用一下你的修建花园的手艺

96
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:19,918
Ah, all is finally revealed.
原来如此

97
00:07:19,941 --> 00:07:23,181
Whit, you are a little predictable.
Whit，你还是很好猜的

98
00:07:25,067 --> 00:07:28,042
The most fun I ever had was working with you.
我最开心的事情就是跟你合作

99
00:07:44,956 --> 00:07:47,879
Anything come up, my dear? Anything at all?
有什么新的，亲爱的？

100
00:07:47,903 --> 00:07:49,828
Nothing suitable.
没有合适的

101
00:07:49,852 --> 00:07:52,111
Is that water or do I need to call Alma?
那是普通的水么？不然我就要给Alma打电话了

102
00:07:52,130 --> 00:07:53,967
Do whatever you want.
爱咋咋地

103
00:07:56,671 --> 00:08:01,532
Anthony Boucher says that this book Psycho by Robert Bloch is
Anthony Boucher说Robert Bloch的《惊魂记》这本书

104
00:08:01,555 --> 00:08:04,281
"fiendishly entertaining."
是“险象环生的娱乐”

105
00:08:04,303 --> 00:08:06,715
It sounds ghastly. Everyone in town's already passed.
听上去蛮恐怖的。城里每个人都不要这个故事。

106
00:08:06,739 --> 00:08:08,699
And who is everyone, pray?
“每个人”都有谁？

107
00:08:08,711 --> 00:08:12,468
The story department finished the coverage this morning.
故事部门今早已经写完了一则新闻

108
00:08:13,826 --> 00:08:17,839
This about Ed Gein, the mass murderer from Wisconsin?
这是关于Ed Gein这个来自Wisconsin的连环杀人凶手么？

109
00:08:17,853 --> 00:08:19,591
Oh, yeah.
没错

110
00:08:19,614 --> 00:08:25,849
"Graphic elements of brutal violence, voyeurism, transvestitism and incest."
“残忍的暴力、窥阴癖、异装癖和乱伦的视觉元素”

111
00:08:25,866 --> 00:08:31,146
Very nice. Not your average run-of-the-mill nutcase, is he?
棒极了！和你的那些平庸的呆瓜完全不一样。

112
00:08:31,170 --> 00:08:33,334
You're kidding.
你开玩笑吧

113
00:08:33,357 --> 00:08:36,805
Peggy, this is the boy who dug up his own mother.
Peggy，这可是一个把自己老妈从坟里挖出来的男生

114
00:08:49,713 --> 00:08:51,862
- Hungry? - Famished.
- 饿了么？ - 饿昏了

115
00:08:51,885 --> 00:08:55,019
You can have half a grapefruit later if you're good.
如果你一会儿感觉还行，只能吃半个葡萄柚

116
00:08:55,042 --> 00:08:56,956
Listen, Hitch.
听，希子

117
00:08:56,980 --> 00:09:00,223
Whit gave me the galleys to his new book yesterday at lunch.
Whit昨天午餐的时候给我了一份他新书的校样

118
00:09:00,247 --> 00:09:03,123
I've already got some ideas about how we can adapt it.
我已经想到一些改编它的好主意

119
00:09:03,147 --> 00:09:06,329
It's elegant. It's sophisticated. It's full of intrigue.
最后会变得非常的高雅、老练以及充满悬念

120
00:09:06,352 --> 00:09:09,454
You mean the book or Mr. Whitfield Cook?
你指的是那本书还是Whitfield Cook本人？

121
00:09:11,626 --> 00:09:13,771
This could be the one, Hitch.
这肯定会一炮而红，小希！

122
00:09:15,468 --> 00:09:17,535
I'll read it later.
我过会儿再读

123
00:09:19,663 --> 00:09:22,323
There are calories in that, you know.
那里面有卡路里你知道么？

124
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:38,887
Ma?
妈？

125
00:09:41,215 --> 00:09:42,401
Ma...
妈...

126
00:09:45,317 --> 00:09:47,869
Aren't you cold?
你不冷么？

127
00:10:12,401 --> 00:10:15,243
No need to be afraid, Ma.
不要怕，妈妈

128
00:10:24,845 --> 00:10:27,123
Oh, God!
我去

129
00:10:27,146 --> 00:10:31,912
I just want you to read this little bit here.
你来读读这一小段

130
00:10:31,936 --> 00:10:35,951
It takes place in the motel bathroom.
它发生在一座汽车旅馆的浴室里

131
00:10:35,963 --> 00:10:38,206
"Mary started to scream,
“Mary尖叫了起来，

132
00:10:38,229 --> 00:10:40,562
"and then the curtains parted further
“帘子被切割到底

133
00:10:40,576 --> 00:10:44,147
"and a hand appeared, holding a butcher's knife.
“一只手从中伸出，手里握着屠夫用的刀子

134
00:10:44,171 --> 00:10:46,824
"It was the knife that, a moment later,
“正是这把刀，在这之后，

135
00:10:46,836 --> 00:10:50,222
cut off her scream, and her head."
切断了尖叫声，还有她的头颅”

136
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:55,213
Charming. Doris Day should do it as a musical.
不错。Doris Day可以把它演成音乐剧

137
00:10:55,237 --> 00:11:00,142
That is nothing but low-budget horror movie claptrap.
这根本就是小成本恐怖电影的俗烂桥段

138
00:11:02,582 --> 00:11:07,276
But what if someone really good made a horror picture?
但是如果交到某个非常擅长于制作惊悚片的人手里呢？

139
00:11:09,559 --> 00:11:12,672
Just think of the shock value.
想想这个惊吓值

140
00:11:12,696 --> 00:11:16,121
Killing off your leading lady halfway through.
在影片一半的时候杀掉女主角

141
00:11:18,237 --> 00:11:21,288
I mean, you are intrigued, are you not, my dear?
我说，你肯定感兴趣了，不是么亲爱的？

142
00:11:22,545 --> 00:11:24,751
Come on, admit it.
矮油，承认吧！

143
00:11:24,774 --> 00:11:27,064
Admit it.
承认吧！

144
00:11:27,087 --> 00:11:29,847
Actually, I think it's a huge mistake.
恰恰相反，我倒是觉得是个巨大的错误

145
00:11:33,657 --> 00:11:37,146
You shouldn't wait till halfway through. Kill her off after thirty minutes.
你完全不需要等到影片的一半。三十分钟后就杀了她

146
00:11:39,745 --> 00:11:41,882
Well!
哈

147
00:11:42,552 --> 00:11:46,360
Peggy, I want you to summon your minions.
Peggy，叫上你的下属们过来

148
00:11:46,384 --> 00:11:49,131
- Minions? - Right away.
- 下属？ - 现在！

149
00:11:49,154 --> 00:11:52,343
Certainly. And who might they be?
可以啊。下属有谁？

150
00:11:52,366 --> 00:11:56,100
Get them started buying copies of Psycho.
让他们将市面上所有的《惊魂记》买回来！

151
00:11:56,124 --> 00:11:59,618
- How many do you need? - All of them. Every copy, nationwide.
- 你要多少本？ - 全部！每一本！全国范围内！

152
00:11:59,642 --> 00:12:02,906
Scour every bookshop, every library. And I mean everywhere.
搜刮所有的书店、图书馆，也就是所有地方。

153
00:12:02,929 --> 00:12:04,879
Psycho is going to be my next movie,
《惊魂记》就是我下一部电影

154
00:12:04,903 --> 00:12:08,417
and I don't want anyone to know the ending until they see it in the theater.
我不想让任何人在看电影前就知道结局

155
00:12:10,659 --> 00:12:13,210
Look at that.
看

156
00:12:15,738 --> 00:12:20,976
Are you sure about this? This is so unlike you.
你确定要做这个？这一点也不是你的风格

157
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:24,048
That is exactly the point, my dear.
这才是重点，亲爱的

158
00:12:27,732 --> 00:12:31,119
Ladies and gentlemen of the press,
敬爱的出版社的各位

159
00:12:34,311 --> 00:12:36,350
good afternoon.
下午好

160
00:12:37,399 --> 00:12:42,041
I see you've all been devouring the article on Mr. Ed Gein.
我看得出来你们一直在阅读这篇关于Ed Gein的文章

161
00:12:42,052 --> 00:12:43,670
Violent chap,
关于一个暴力的男子

162
00:12:43,694 --> 00:12:48,457
and the real-life inspiration behind Psycho.
以及这本书背后的我的真实的灵感

163
00:12:48,477 --> 00:12:53,686
All of us harbor dark recesses of violence,
我们所有人心底之龛都隐蔽这暴力

164
00:12:53,709 --> 00:12:56,633
and horror.
和恐惧。

165
00:12:56,656 --> 00:12:59,573
Fascinating, isn't it?
精彩吧？

166
00:12:59,597 --> 00:13:05,045
When the Wisconsin Police Department raided Mr. Gein's farm,
当Wisconsin警察局突袭了Gein先生的农场后，

167
00:13:05,068 --> 00:13:09,464
they opened the door... And voila!
他们打开门。然后，哇！

168
00:13:09,489 --> 00:13:15,137
They discovered ten female heads with the tops sawn off.
他们发现十个顶部被锯平的女性头颅

169
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:17,987
Pass these around, would you? And have a look.
请你传阅一下好么？

170
00:13:18,010 --> 00:13:20,476
Masks of human skin.
这是人皮面具

171
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:24,284
A pair of lips on a drawstring for a window shade.
窗帘的拉绳上有一对嘴唇

172
00:13:24,308 --> 00:13:27,037
Oh, yes, and a jug containing human noses.
啊对了，还有一个装满鼻子的罐子

173
00:13:27,060 --> 00:13:30,606
Is this really going to be your next picture, Mr. Hitchcock?
这真是是你下一部电影吗，希区柯克先生？

174
00:13:30,630 --> 00:13:33,138
Well, that is my intention, yes, madam.
嗯是的夫人，那我的打算

175
00:13:33,161 --> 00:13:38,844
My only wish is that Ed Gein looked a little more like William Holden instead of Elmer Fudd.
我唯一的希望就是Ed Gein看起来更像William Holden而不是Elmer Fudd

176
00:13:41,975 --> 00:13:46,074
By the way, try the finger sandwiches. They're real fingers.
说起来，试试手指三明治。里面可是夹着真的手指。

177
00:13:47,313 --> 00:13:50,522
Bloody hell!
我了个去

178
00:13:50,546 --> 00:13:52,647
Now don't pretend you're not upset he hasn't read it.
你别假装不对他没读你的剧本而生气了

179
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:54,744
I'm not. I'm a big boy, I can take it.
我没有生气。我是个大男孩了，可以接受这一切

180
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:56,529
Well, I loved it.
我很喜欢你的作品呢

181
00:13:56,552 --> 00:13:59,657
It must be great fun to research.
研究起来肯定非常有趣

182
00:13:59,681 --> 00:14:02,339
Do you really think he will read it?
你真的觉得他会读一下么？

183
00:14:02,351 --> 00:14:05,075
Ah, speak of the devil.
啊，说曹操曹操到

184
00:14:05,087 --> 00:14:09,161
Hitch, I ran all over town trying to find a copy of Psycho
阿希啊，我跑遍全城想找一本《惊魂记》来看看

185
00:14:09,185 --> 00:14:11,415
but I simply cannot find one.
可是我连一本都找不到。

186
00:14:11,439 --> 00:14:16,029
- I wonder how that could have happened. - Yeah.
- 我也想知道为什么会这样 - 好吧

187
00:14:16,041 --> 00:14:18,818
Don't stop looking on my behalf.
你为了我也得继续找下去

188
00:14:18,842 --> 00:14:21,354
Hitch, you should come.
希区先生，你应该来一下

189
00:14:27,392 --> 00:14:31,033
I've seen happier faces on a school bus going over a cliff.
校车路过悬崖孩子们都比这个高兴

190
00:14:33,674 --> 00:14:37,453
But they can't stop looking, can they?
但是他们没法不看，对吧？

191
00:14:43,348 --> 00:14:46,047
Audiences want to be shocked, Barney.
观众想被惊吓，Barney

192
00:14:46,071 --> 00:14:48,642
They want something different.
他们想要新意

193
00:14:48,654 --> 00:14:50,286
And this is it.
所以就是这了

194
00:14:50,310 --> 00:14:53,726
Every time you want to do something different
每一次你想做些有新意的事情

195
00:14:53,749 --> 00:14:58,185
like The Wrong Man or Vertigo, someone loses money.
像《申冤记》或者《迷魂记》，总有人会亏钱

196
00:14:58,210 --> 00:15:01,498
So we should stop trying to give them something new?
所以我们就不能做有新意的事情了么

197
00:15:01,522 --> 00:15:04,718
You owe Paramount one last picture, Hitch.
你还差派拉蒙最后一部电影

198
00:15:04,742 --> 00:15:07,771
Can't you do something like North by Northwest
你就不能做一部像《西北偏北》这样的电影

199
00:15:07,795 --> 00:15:11,163
but for us this time instead of for MGM?
而且是为我们做一部，而不是为米高梅

200
00:15:13,751 --> 00:15:15,956
Psycho.
就做《惊魂记》

201
00:15:19,132 --> 00:15:22,673
No one respects the name Hitchcock like Paramount.
没有人比派拉蒙更尊重希区柯克这四个字

202
00:15:24,991 --> 00:15:28,894
Are you telling me "no," Barney?
你的意思是不接受么，Barney？

203
00:15:28,917 --> 00:15:31,923
I think you know me better than that, Hitch.
我觉得你没明白我的意思

204
00:15:34,306 --> 00:15:35,879
What a putz.
这算什么

205
00:15:35,891 --> 00:15:39,251
You know what his family did before they built those movie palaces?
你知道他的家族在创建这些电影宫殿之前是做什么的？

206
00:15:39,274 --> 00:15:41,440
Ran a grocery store.
开杂货店的

207
00:15:41,464 --> 00:15:45,491
My father ran a grocery store.
我父亲也曾经营杂货店

208
00:15:45,515 --> 00:15:49,252
Exactly. That's what I'm saying. He should show some respect.
对啊，这正是我想说的，他应该表现出更多的尊重

209
00:15:50,814 --> 00:15:54,731
They think I've lost my touch, Lew.
他们觉得我江郎才尽了，Lew

210
00:15:54,755 --> 00:15:58,923
My association with television has cheapened me.
我和电视界的交情在他们看来使我贬值了

211
00:15:58,946 --> 00:16:01,071
Are you referring to that deal I got you
你指的是我那次帮你找的机会

212
00:16:01,095 --> 00:16:04,873
where Bristol-Meyers pays you 29 grand
an episode and you own the negative?
Bristol-Meyers付你2万9千一集的薪酬，并且底片仍属于你自己

213
00:16:04,896 --> 00:16:07,296
That's my kind of cheap.
我倒觉得这才是贬值

214
00:16:07,318 --> 00:16:11,151
They just want the same thing over and over and over.
我总是反反复复追求同一个风格

215
00:16:11,175 --> 00:16:14,880
They've put me in a coffin and now they're nailing down the lid.
他们已经将我放在一副棺材里而现在正想把棺材盖钉死

216
00:16:14,903 --> 00:16:19,065
Hitch, as your agent, I will never let that happen.
希区柯克，我作为你的经纪人，绝对不会让这件事发生的

217
00:16:23,307 --> 00:16:26,989
How much you think you can make this picture for?
你估计需要多少钱

218
00:16:27,012 --> 00:16:29,770
$800,000, give or take.
多多少少八十万

219
00:16:38,544 --> 00:16:40,920
You're home early.
你今天回家挺早的

220
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:46,192
Oh, it's lovely actually.
噢，这其实挺好的

221
00:16:57,070 --> 00:17:02,330
You know, I'm disappointed you didn't give Whit's book a chance.
你没给Whit的书一个机会让我还蛮失落的

222
00:17:02,353 --> 00:17:04,498
And what about Whit? Is he disappointed?
Whit怎么想？他失落么？

223
00:17:04,522 --> 00:17:06,846
Oh, no. He knows you well enough.
他不会，他知道你的作风

224
00:17:06,869 --> 00:17:10,814
Look at that! Time for a new one anyway.
哎呀你看看这件衣服。反正也该买件新的。

225
00:17:10,838 --> 00:17:14,233
Well you'd better enjoy the pool, my dear, while you can.
你应该多用用这池塘，亲爱的，特别是趁你腿脚还利索的时候

226
00:17:16,835 --> 00:17:20,311
We might not have it much longer.
《惊魂记》可能拍不下去了

227
00:17:20,335 --> 00:17:21,732
Why?
为什么？

228
00:17:21,755 --> 00:17:24,889
Paramount refuses to finance the movie.
派拉蒙不愿意投资

229
00:17:24,913 --> 00:17:28,487
Oh, Hitch, I'm so sorry.
噢，小希，好遗憾啊

230
00:17:28,511 --> 00:17:33,024
Lew can't find the money. At least, not fast enough.
Lew还没能找到资金。或者说，没那么快能找到资金

231
00:17:33,041 --> 00:17:34,558
Well why not wait?
为什么不等一段时间呢？

232
00:17:36,429 --> 00:17:38,070
No.
不行

233
00:17:40,712 --> 00:17:45,811
Just going to have to go it alone, old girl.
可能要不得不要独立出片了，老女孩

234
00:17:45,835 --> 00:17:48,209
Finance it ourselves.
自己投资

235
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:59,019
Are we going to have to sell the whole house or just the pool?
你是想卖掉整套房子呢，还是只卖这个池塘。

236
00:18:00,563 --> 00:18:03,571
I just want to do the film.
我只是想把这电影拍出来

237
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:13,223
I will ask you this once and I'll never mention it again.
我只问一次这个问题

238
00:18:14,503 --> 00:18:16,857
Why this one, Hitch?
为什么现在一定要拍《惊魂记》？

239
00:18:18,759 --> 00:18:22,573
It's not just because so many people are saying "no," is it?
不仅仅是因为那么多人说“不同意”吧？

240
00:18:24,137 --> 00:18:28,165
Do you remember the fun we had when we started out all those years ago?
你还记得当年我们刚开始做电影时的快乐么

241
00:18:29,685 --> 00:18:32,249
We didn't have any money then, did we?
当时我们一分钱没有，不是么？

242
00:18:32,270 --> 00:18:35,753
We didn't have any time, either, but we took risks, do you remember?
时间我们也没有多少。但是我们愿意冒险，你还记得吗？

243
00:18:37,674 --> 00:18:44,920
We experimented. We invented new ways of making pictures
我们做试验，我们创造出新的制作电影的方法

244
00:18:44,944 --> 00:18:47,430
because we had to.
因为我们必须得这样做

245
00:18:50,013 --> 00:18:56,206
I want to feel that kind of freedom again.
我只是想再找回那种自由感

246
00:18:59,060 --> 00:19:01,414
Like we used to, you know?
就像我们当年那样，你明白么？

247
00:19:07,683 --> 00:19:13,694
We are about to propose a restructured deal for Psycho.
我们打算做一个重建《惊魂记》提议

248
00:19:13,718 --> 00:19:16,031
I'm listening.
说吧

249
00:19:16,043 --> 00:19:20,312
We finance it independently.
我们自己独立出资

250
00:19:20,335 --> 00:19:25,518
Hitch waives his directorial fee. Paramount only distributes it,
阿希放弃他的导演费用。派拉蒙只负责发行，

251
00:19:25,542 --> 00:19:29,203
in exchange for 40% of the profits.
40%的收益归派拉蒙所有（但愿没翻译错）

252
00:19:29,226 --> 00:19:34,440
Interesting. But what exactly is Paramount distributing?
有意思。但是派拉蒙为什么发行？

253
00:19:34,463 --> 00:19:38,790
Is this still a picture about a queer killing people in his mother's dress?
这不还是那部怪胎穿着妈妈的裙子干谋杀的电影么？

254
00:19:38,813 --> 00:19:42,690
What this picture is about is the reputation of Alfred Hitchcock.
这部电影其实是代表了希区柯克的名声

255
00:19:42,713 --> 00:19:46,283
- No one is arguing that. - Barney,
- 没人不同意这一点 - Barney

256
00:19:46,306 --> 00:19:49,488
it's very simple.
其实很简单

257
00:19:49,512 --> 00:19:52,545
This is Mr. Hitchcock's next film.
这就是希区柯克下一部电影

258
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:57,142
Are you in or are you out?
干不干这一票，你决定

259
00:20:02,328 --> 00:20:06,312
Fine. We'll take that deal.
好，派拉蒙同意

260
00:20:08,199 --> 00:20:10,895
If you can get the money.
只要你能筹到钱

261
00:20:10,919 --> 00:20:14,018
We already have the money, Barney.
我们已经有足够的钱了，Barney

262
00:20:20,607 --> 00:20:23,991
Who do I make it out to?
支票应该开给谁？

263
00:20:29,034 --> 00:20:32,357
If this picture fails, Alma,
如果这部电影不卖座，Alma

264
00:20:32,381 --> 00:20:37,500
we'll be in for a long, humiliating bout of crow-eating.
我们会吃很长一段时间的丢人的闭门羹

265
00:20:39,741 --> 00:20:44,720
- It'll be splendid. - Are you sure?
- 会很精彩的 - 你确定？

266
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:49,871
Of the movie? Not at all.
电影？从来没这么觉得

267
00:20:49,895 --> 00:20:54,291
But of you? Unquestionably.
但是希区柯克？毫无疑问的

268
00:21:00,679 --> 00:21:02,100
Ahem.
咳

269
00:21:03,990 --> 00:21:06,738
- Joe Stefano. Good to meet you. - Sit down.
- 我是Joe Stefano，很高兴见到你 - 坐下吧

270
00:21:06,761 --> 00:21:08,323
I'm sorry I was late.
抱歉我迟到了

271
00:21:08,346 --> 00:21:10,542
My shrink session went overtime.
我被心理诊疗的时间延误了

272
00:21:13,624 --> 00:21:16,701
I see him every day and it's still not enough.
我每天都去他那儿，但还是不够

273
00:21:16,725 --> 00:21:20,511
I thought it was only director's assistants who needed psychiatrists,
我以为只有导演助理才需要去看精神科医生

274
00:21:20,523 --> 00:21:22,730
not writers.
而不是编剧

275
00:21:27,143 --> 00:21:29,467
Do you see a shrink, Mr. Hitchcock?
你会去看心理医生么，希区柯克先生？

276
00:21:29,491 --> 00:21:32,228
I have to confess, Mr. Stefano,
我必须承认，Stefano先生

277
00:21:32,252 --> 00:21:34,846
It boggles my brain just trying to imagine.
幻想才是烦恼我大脑的东西

278
00:21:34,869 --> 00:21:37,863
What you and your shrink could possibly talk about every day?
你和你的心理医生每天都说些什么内容？

279
00:21:41,007 --> 00:21:45,206
The usual: Sex. Rage. My mother.
老三样：性、强奸和我妈

280
00:21:55,124 --> 00:21:57,466
Good morning, sir.
早上好，先生

281
00:21:59,929 --> 00:22:01,091
Let me have a look at you.
让我检查下你

282
00:22:01,115 --> 00:22:05,920
The only thing worse than a visit to the dentist is a visit to censor.
比看牙医还糟糕的事情只有见审查员了

283
00:22:05,943 --> 00:22:08,855
Whatever you do, Hitch, don't lose your temper.
不管怎么样，你都要控制好情绪

284
00:22:10,677 --> 00:22:12,382
- See you later. - Good luck.
- 再见 - 祝你好运

285
00:22:15,358 --> 00:22:18,975
The Code will absolutely not permit you
（海斯）法典肯定不允许你的这部电影

286
00:22:18,998 --> 00:22:22,227
to show a knife penetrating a woman's flesh.
有一把刀插入女性的身体

287
00:22:22,251 --> 00:22:24,056
I assure you, Geoffrey,
我向你保证，Geoffrey

288
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:29,317
my murders are always models of taste and discretion.
我的杀人犯一直是品味和谨慎的典范

289
00:22:29,341 --> 00:22:32,954
Is there any improper suggestion of nudity in this
电影会有不恰当的裸体暗示

290
00:22:32,978 --> 00:22:35,223
murder scene in the shower?
在这段浴室谋杀戏当中么？

291
00:22:35,247 --> 00:22:39,335
She won't be nude. She'll be wearing a shower cap.
女主角不会裸体，她会带着浴帽。。。

292
00:22:44,395 --> 00:22:47,659
We might accept a shot from outside the bathroom window
我们也许允许一个从浴室窗户外面拍摄的

293
00:22:47,683 --> 00:22:50,042
of Marion in silhouette above the shoulders.
Marion的过肩黑色轮廓的镜头，

294
00:22:50,066 --> 00:22:52,848
Provided that the glass is frosted.
而且还要在窗户有雾气的情况下

295
00:22:53,602 --> 00:22:55,281
Thank you.
感激不尽

296
00:22:55,304 --> 00:22:59,647
And the scene with the toilet.
然后还有那场厕所的戏

297
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:02,118
It is completely necessary to show the toilet,
真的非常有必要拍摄厕所

298
00:23:02,141 --> 00:23:05,602
because Marion Crane attempts to flush evidence down it.
因为Marion Crane尝试在马桶冲掉所有的证据

299
00:23:05,621 --> 00:23:08,615
Remnants of which are later discovered by her sister.
而未被处理掉的证据在这之后会被女主人公的姐姐发现

300
00:23:08,639 --> 00:23:14,641
These remnants, you understand, are clues to her vanishing.
这些证据，你要明白，是她无故消失的线索

301
00:23:14,664 --> 00:23:19,505
No American movie has ever found it necessary to show a toilet,
没有美国电影觉得有必要展示厕所

302
00:23:19,528 --> 00:23:21,818
let alone to flush one.
更别说冲厕所了

303
00:23:21,842 --> 00:23:24,935
Perhaps we ought to shoot the film in France
我想应该在法国拍这电影

304
00:23:24,936 --> 00:23:27,540
and use a bidet instead.
用（洗生殖器和臀部用的）坐浴盆来替代马桶

305
00:23:30,712 --> 00:23:36,003
Mr. Hitchcock, if this office denies you a seal,
希区柯克先生，如果本部门送你一个禁映

306
00:23:36,027 --> 00:23:38,569
and we're certainly heading in that direction,
而且我们现在看起来也正往这个方向上走去

307
00:23:38,592 --> 00:23:44,159
your movie will not be released in a single theater in this country.
你的电影将不会有资格在这个国家任何一个电影院上映

308
00:23:44,183 --> 00:23:47,086
Will you be making jokes then?
到那时你再开玩笑吧

309
00:23:49,063 --> 00:23:52,877
Everyone in Hollywood resents me.
每个在好莱坞的人都恨我

310
00:23:52,901 --> 00:23:55,255
I make them millions of dollars,
我为他们赚了成千上万的钱

311
00:23:55,279 --> 00:24:00,058
and every year I sit at those dreadful award show dinners,
而且每年还要参加那些无聊的颁奖晚宴

312
00:24:00,081 --> 00:24:04,205
waiting for someone just to say, "You're good."
等着某个人来说一句“你真牛”

313
00:24:06,335 --> 00:24:11,835
They take sadistic pleasure in denying me that one little moment.
他们从拒绝我的那一瞬间中获取病态的快乐

314
00:24:11,858 --> 00:24:13,981
That must hurt.
那一定很受伤

315
00:24:16,390 --> 00:24:20,954
Deeply, Ed. Deeply.
伤得很深，Ed，非常深

316
00:24:21,873 --> 00:24:27,521
Sorry, doctor. I'm just not used to this...
不好意思，医生。我只是不习惯这个

317
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:30,434
process.
过程

318
00:24:31,569 --> 00:24:35,158
Just think of me more like a friend.
就把我想象成你个朋友

319
00:24:35,181 --> 00:24:39,385
It's just that more and more I've been having these...
这些冲动我到现在为止变得越来越多

320
00:24:39,408 --> 00:24:40,571
impulses.

321
00:24:45,136 --> 00:24:48,104
What kind of impulses?
什么冲动？

322
00:24:53,494 --> 00:24:55,749
Strong ones.
强烈的冲动

323
00:25:14,596 --> 00:25:16,028
Here.
这个

324
00:25:16,745 --> 00:25:19,492
The Lazar Office tell me he's crazy to work with you.
Lazar告诉我他非常想和你合作

325
00:25:19,516 --> 00:25:23,543
Tell Swifty Lazar he should not have overexposed his client on television.
告诉他他不应该让他的客户在电视上过分曝光

326
00:25:23,567 --> 00:25:26,164
Unlike some we could mention.
不像有一些事情我们可以提一下

327
00:25:28,681 --> 00:25:31,867
- Anthony Perkins. - Oh...
- Anthony Perkins - 噢。。

328
00:25:31,891 --> 00:25:35,106
Think of the duality he could bring to the role of Norman.
想想他能给角色Norman带去多少的二重性

329
00:25:35,124 --> 00:25:37,697
The rage lurking beneath that little boy grin.
多少暴戾隐藏在这个小男孩的笑容里

330
00:25:37,722 --> 00:25:41,339
The winsome charm he uses to keep from being found out.
他的迷人气质让人从不察觉到他的秘密

331
00:25:41,362 --> 00:25:45,859
Why, Alma, you're not suggesting Mr. Perkins is...?
为什么，Alma？你不会是在暗示Perkins先生是？

332
00:25:45,883 --> 00:25:47,562
Hm.
嗯~

333
00:25:48,936 --> 00:25:50,745
What?
什么？

334
00:25:56,583 --> 00:25:58,829
I like your office.
我喜欢你的办公室

335
00:26:01,796 --> 00:26:06,680
I can't count how many times I've seen Strangers on a Train.
我已经数不过来看过多少次《火车怪客》了

336
00:26:06,704 --> 00:26:09,476
And Rope.
还有《夺魂索》

337
00:26:09,499 --> 00:26:15,012
Well, Norman Bates is the logical extension of those two characters in that movie.
好吧。Norman Bates合理延伸了刚才你提到的那种电影当中两个主角

338
00:26:15,033 --> 00:26:18,873
Appealing, sensitive, suffering the terrible burden
他很诱人、敏感、承受着

339
00:26:18,896 --> 00:26:22,430
of being forced to pretend to be something he is not.
被迫假装不属于他的一个身份的折磨

340
00:26:25,877 --> 00:26:30,362
I'm sick of all this romantic crap the studios keep shoving me into.
我已经受不了这些制片公司硬塞给我的浪漫陈词滥调的角色

341
00:26:30,374 --> 00:26:33,262
But my only worry is,
但是我唯一担心的是

342
00:26:33,286 --> 00:26:36,589
well, playing Norman might cut too close to home.
嗯，饰演Norman也许太相似于我的过去了

343
00:26:38,049 --> 00:26:40,070
How so?
为什么？

344
00:26:42,689 --> 00:26:49,417
When I was younger, I was incredibly close to my mother.
在我年轻的时候，我非常黏我的母亲

345
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:53,759
So close that I remember wishing my father would drop dead.
黏到我以至于非常希望父亲可以就此死掉

346
00:26:55,463 --> 00:26:59,669
And then when I was five, he did just that.
而我爸确实死了，在我五岁的时候

347
00:26:59,693 --> 00:27:01,970
He keeled over from a heart attack.
死于心脏病

348
00:27:08,813 --> 00:27:12,681
You see I've been guilty my whole life, Mr. Hitchcock.
我一直有罪恶感，希区柯克先生

349
00:27:17,961 --> 00:27:20,775
You know, I'm getting blisters just watching you.
你知道么，我光是看着你做这些就能起水泡

350
00:27:20,799 --> 00:27:22,337
Oh, stop complaining.
噢，别抱怨了

351
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:25,261
A bit of fresh air and exercise will do you good.
新鲜空气和运动对你是有好处的

352
00:27:25,284 --> 00:27:28,945
- I'm going to have a drink. - No you're not. You're going to finish that hedge.
- 我去喝点东西 - 不，不行。你要去搞定那个篱笆

353
00:27:28,956 --> 00:27:31,667
You've got to go all the way around there, all the way around there, all the way around there.
你要修好所有的

354
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:33,996
- It's impossible. I can't do that. - Yes you can.
- 这不可能，我没法做完 - 你可以

355
00:27:36,620 --> 00:27:41,274
You know, I was thinking, if I could get Grace Kelly to play the girl,
你知道，我在想，如果我能让Grace Kelly饰演女主角

356
00:27:41,298 --> 00:27:43,458
they'd let me get away with murder.
他们就会让我拍凶杀戏

357
00:27:43,482 --> 00:27:47,433
Well you can't. She's a princess now, which makes her permanently unattainable.
这不可能。她是公主，这就意味着你根本请不到她

358
00:27:47,457 --> 00:27:49,758
And all the more desirable.
这让我更想要她了

359
00:27:49,781 --> 00:27:53,283
What about Deborah Kerr? Lew mentioned her.
Deborah Kerr怎么样？Lew提起过她

360
00:27:53,306 --> 00:27:55,440
No, she's too Scottish.
不行，她太苏格兰化了

361
00:27:57,025 --> 00:27:59,527
What about Janet Leigh?
诶，Janet怎么样？

362
00:27:59,551 --> 00:28:03,807
I know she's normally the "good girl," but she was awfully good in Touch of Evil.
我知道她基本上算是一个乖乖女，但是她在《历劫佳人》里表现得太出色了

363
00:28:03,831 --> 00:28:08,230
You remember how you always used to remark on her figure at the Wassermans' parties?
你还记得在Wassermans的派对上你曾经“提到”过她的身材么？

364
00:28:09,646 --> 00:28:11,401
Yeah.
对诶

365
00:28:17,112 --> 00:28:19,188
- Good evening. - Hello.
- 晚上好 - 你好

366
00:28:19,213 --> 00:28:21,105
- Lovely to see you. - Charmed.
- 很高兴见到你 - 你真迷人

367
00:28:21,128 --> 00:28:23,124
- Hi. - Hello, Janet. How are you?
- 你好 - 你好，Janet

368
00:28:23,148 --> 00:28:25,062
Wonderful to see you.
见到你太好了

369
00:28:25,085 --> 00:28:28,918
- Well, my dear, you look very beautiful. - Thank you.
- 亲爱的，你看起来太漂亮了 - 谢谢

370
00:28:28,942 --> 00:28:30,996
Very beautiful.
真的非常漂亮

371
00:28:34,916 --> 00:28:39,300
Of course the real secret of Mrs. Simpson's appeal to the Duke of Windsor
当然了，Simpson女士之所以会喜欢Windsor公爵的真实原因在于

372
00:28:39,323 --> 00:28:43,132
was that she could make a toothpick feel like a cigar.
她可以将一支雪茄变得像一支雪茄

373
00:28:44,717 --> 00:28:47,674
Oh, I've been so immersed in preparing to play Marion
噢。我一直非常投入准备扮演Marion

374
00:28:47,698 --> 00:28:50,121
I'd almost forgotten how to laugh.
我都快忘记怎么大笑了

375
00:28:50,144 --> 00:28:51,512
- Oh, really? - Yes.
- 是么？ - 是的

376
00:28:51,536 --> 00:28:54,889
Now, now, you must try the banana shortcake.
现在，你必须尝尝这里的香蕉油酥糕饼

377
00:28:54,903 --> 00:28:57,791
Oh, no. Nothing for me, thank you. I'm watching my figure.
噢，不了，我吃不动了。谢谢。我必须要照顾好我的身材。

378
00:28:57,815 --> 00:29:00,755
Yes, you're not the only one. We're fine, thank you.
是的，不仅仅只有你需要照顾。我们不用了，谢谢。

379
00:29:00,779 --> 00:29:02,567
George, bring her the banana shortcake.
George，给她来一份香蕉油酥糕饼

380
00:29:02,591 --> 00:29:05,984
In fact, make that two large portions. Thank you.
呃等会儿，两份大的吧。谢谢

381
00:29:06,008 --> 00:29:10,381
Now tell me, my dear, how else have you prepared for the part of Marion Crane?
告诉我亲爱的，你还为Marion Crane准备了什么？

382
00:29:10,404 --> 00:29:12,859
Well, I've written an entire history for her,
嗯，我写下了她的整个历程

383
00:29:12,882 --> 00:29:16,457
which seems a little silly, I know, but it really does help.
这看起来确实有点傻，我知道，可还是很有用的

384
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:19,099
- It doesn't sound silly at all. - No?
- 一点都不傻 - 真的？

385
00:29:19,116 --> 00:29:22,648
Why don't you tell us one of her deepest secrets?
要不你告诉我们她其中一个深藏的秘密

386
00:29:25,067 --> 00:29:28,360
Well, she leads a double life.
她活在一个双重世界里

387
00:29:28,383 --> 00:29:31,824
At the Lowery Office, she wears Tweed perfume.
在Lowery办公室，她喷着Tweed香水

388
00:29:31,847 --> 00:29:34,172
But when she's with Sam,
但是当她和Sam在一起时

389
00:29:34,196 --> 00:29:38,775
she recklessly breaks out her most expensive bottle.
她想都不想就用起了她最贵的香水

390
00:29:38,799 --> 00:29:41,170
"My Sin" by Lanvin.
Lanvin的“我的罪恶”

391
00:29:42,407 --> 00:29:43,874
- "My Sin"? - Yes.
- “我的罪恶”？- 对的

392
00:29:43,898 --> 00:29:45,861
Good Lord!
上帝啊

393
00:29:45,877 --> 00:29:48,643
I do have a concern or two.
我确实有一两个顾虑

394
00:29:48,667 --> 00:29:52,892
I'm an actress, of course, but I'm first a wife and a mother.
我是一名女演员，这点没错，但是我首先还是一个妻子和母亲

395
00:29:52,916 --> 00:29:56,145
And I'm just curious to know...
我只是出于好奇而想了解一下

396
00:29:56,168 --> 00:29:58,894
How are you going to shoot this shower scene?
你想怎么拍摄这场浴室戏？

397
00:29:58,918 --> 00:30:01,642
Yes, you and the Shurlock Office.
是的，你还有福尔摩斯

398
00:30:01,665 --> 00:30:06,843
It's only that, well, from here up, I'm not exactly boyish.
如果只是，要拍上半身全身，嗯，我还没那么爷们儿

399
00:30:06,867 --> 00:30:10,079
Allow me to set your mind at rest, my dear.
允许我让你放松一下，亲爱的

400
00:30:10,102 --> 00:30:13,578
I will be shooting short bits of film from various angles.
我将会拍摄好几个不同角度的短镜头

401
00:30:13,601 --> 00:30:17,693
Cut together, the montage will only suggest nudity.
最后剪辑在一起，蒙太奇会暗示出裸露的信息

402
00:30:17,716 --> 00:30:19,124
Suggest violence.
还有暗示的暴力

403
00:30:19,147 --> 00:30:21,533
Nothing will actually be shown.
不会真的裸露出来

404
00:30:22,646 --> 00:30:25,545
But of course, having you in the shower
不过当然了，如果能够有一场你的洗浴的戏

405
00:30:25,557 --> 00:30:29,807
would make it all the more, well, titillating.
会让这部分，嗯，更加挑逗

406
00:30:31,568 --> 00:30:33,351
Will you excuse me?
我先离开一下

407
00:30:48,937 --> 00:30:51,508
Alma, dear, how lovely to see you.
Alma，怎么在这里见到你了

408
00:30:51,532 --> 00:30:53,986
Oh, hello, Lillian.
噢，你好，Lillian

409
00:30:54,009 --> 00:30:55,829
You're looking a little pale.
你气色看起来不怎么样啊

410
00:30:55,853 --> 00:30:59,194
No wonder with that thing your husband's working on now.
这也不奇怪，因为你丈夫做的那么诡异的事情

411
00:30:59,214 --> 00:31:01,426
You can't possibly approve.
你肯定不同意的

412
00:31:01,450 --> 00:31:04,623
Why are you letting him do something so tasteless?
干嘛要让他做这么没有品位的事情

413
00:31:04,647 --> 00:31:08,314
Don't upset yourself, darling. It's only a bloody movie.
亲爱的，你倒是干嘛那么气色差？这无非就是一部电影

414
00:31:25,155 --> 00:31:29,159
I can't believe you made Vera Miles play the sister.
你居然让Vera Miles演姐姐

415
00:31:29,171 --> 00:31:32,998
Well, I've still got her under contract. May as well get something out of her.
反正她还在合同期内，总要用一下她不是么

416
00:31:33,021 --> 00:31:35,786
Rather a thankless role, don't you think?
她可是一个从来不领情的人，你难道不觉得么？

417
00:31:35,809 --> 00:31:38,660
For an utterly thankless girl.
是非常的不领情

418
00:31:51,538 --> 00:31:53,229
Horrible.
太倒胃口了

419
00:31:53,253 --> 00:31:55,977
The old man really is unhappy with me, isn't he?
那个老家伙真的对我不满呢

420
00:31:56,001 --> 00:31:58,779
Wait till you see the undergarments he has picked out for you.
等下你先试试他给你挑的内衣

421
00:32:00,929 --> 00:32:05,091
Okay. Well, I am just going to have to keep telling myself,
这样，好吧。我就告诉自己

422
00:32:05,114 --> 00:32:08,854
one more picture and I'm free as a bird.
这是给他拍的最后一部电影，之后我就自由了

423
00:32:22,679 --> 00:32:26,465
So I've made a list of places where we can tighten our belts.
我做好了一份我们哪儿可以节省的清单？

424
00:32:26,483 --> 00:32:28,256
Huh?
啊？

425
00:32:28,978 --> 00:32:32,460
We could all learn the art of self-restraint, couldn't we, Alfred?
我们都可以学习一下节俭的技巧，不是么阿弗？

426
00:32:33,822 --> 00:32:37,970
Gardeners once a week, weekend off for the driver...
一周只请一次园丁、周末不请司机

427
00:32:37,994 --> 00:32:41,287
No, that's impossible. We'll have to find other places to cut.
这怎么行。我们还是找别的方面来节流吧

428
00:32:41,311 --> 00:32:43,131
There aren't any other places.
没有其他方面了

429
00:32:43,143 --> 00:32:47,333
And there's be no more shipments flown in from Maxim's of Paris.
然后，还有从巴黎的Maxim's运来的货物我们也得放弃

430
00:32:47,368 --> 00:32:49,700
We can't afford it.
我们付不起了

431
00:32:49,723 --> 00:32:52,618
The foie gras at Chasen's is more than adequate.
Chasen's的鹅肝我们也吃不起了

432
00:32:52,642 --> 00:32:56,653
But those geese are from Barstow, not from Marseilles.
但是那些鹅是从Barstow来的，又不是从Marseilles

433
00:32:56,677 --> 00:33:01,878
Yes, well we all have to make our sacrifices for the greater good, don't we, Alfred?
我们都要为了实现长远的目标牺牲一下不是么阿弗？

434
00:33:35,615 --> 00:33:37,989
I'll go get the knives.
我去拿下刀子

435
00:34:00,885 --> 00:34:03,729
Am I making a terrible mistake?
我错了么？

436
00:34:06,979 --> 00:34:09,691
What if it's another Vertigo?
要是这只是又一部《迷魂记》怎么办？

437
00:34:09,714 --> 00:34:13,234
Just get the first take under your belt. You'll be fine.
你先拍下第一个镜头，一切都会好起来的

438
00:34:23,210 --> 00:34:25,776
Are you decent, my dear?
穿好衣服了么亲爱的？

439
00:34:27,064 --> 00:34:29,107
- Good morning. - Good morning.
- 早上好 - 早上好

440
00:34:29,131 --> 00:34:31,766
Am I all right?
我还行吧？

441
00:34:31,778 --> 00:34:34,807
- Perfect. - Wow.
- 完美极了 - 哇

442
00:34:34,831 --> 00:34:36,439
- Morning. - Morning.
- 早上好 - 早上好

443
00:34:36,463 --> 00:34:39,313
I want to thank you once again for this opportunity, Mr. Hitchcock.
我还想再谢谢你能给我这个机会，希区柯克先生

444
00:34:39,332 --> 00:34:41,412
You may call me "Hitch." Hold the cock.
你可以叫我希胖，把“柯克”去掉

445
00:34:41,435 --> 00:34:44,699
Well look at you two. America's favorite boy and girl next door.
好了，看看你们俩，美国最受欢迎的邻家男孩女孩

446
00:34:44,723 --> 00:34:46,917
Yes, and we're about to move to a whole new neighborhood.
是啊，现在又要搬进一座新的“邻家”

447
00:34:46,940 --> 00:34:49,899
- Morning, Janet. Morning, Tony. - Morning, Vera.
- Janet、Tony早上好 - 早上好Vera

448
00:34:49,922 --> 00:34:52,482
- Thanks for the wardrobe, Hitch. - Do you approve?
- 谢谢你的衣服 - 你真的喜欢么？

449
00:34:52,505 --> 00:34:54,343
You're the genius.
你的品味最好了

450
00:34:54,364 --> 00:34:57,194
One thing, though. My script is missing its last ten pages.
还有一件事就是，我的剧本最后十页怎么没了？

451
00:34:57,217 --> 00:35:01,659
Everyone's script is missing ten pages until Alma finishes the revisions.
等我的Alma把剧本修订完了，所有人呢的剧本才能补上最后十页

452
00:35:01,682 --> 00:35:04,019
You're just in time for the Oath.
你们刚好赶上宣誓

453
00:35:04,042 --> 00:35:07,571
- The what? - The Oath.
- 什么？ - 宣誓

454
00:35:07,595 --> 00:35:10,765
- Good morning, everyone. - Good morning.
- 早上好各位 - 早上好

455
00:35:10,789 --> 00:35:14,029
Would you all raise your right hands?
麻烦各位举起你们的右手

456
00:35:14,053 --> 00:35:16,378
That includes you, Vera Miles.
你也一样，Vera Miles

457
00:35:19,138 --> 00:35:22,379
- I do solemnly promise... - I do solemnly promise...
- 我郑重地承诺 - 我郑重地承诺

458
00:35:22,403 --> 00:35:25,955
- That I will not divulge... - That I will not divulge...
我不会把

459
00:35:25,979 --> 00:35:32,399
- The plot nor the many secrets of Psycho... - The plot nor the many secrets of Psycho...
《惊魂记》的剧情和秘密泄露给

460
00:35:32,422 --> 00:35:36,309
- To friends, relatives... - To friends, relatives...
朋友、亲人

461
00:35:36,333 --> 00:35:38,771
- Trade reporters... - Trade reporters...
记者

462
00:35:38,795 --> 00:35:43,053
Not even outgoing President Dwight D. Eisenhower.
甚至透露给快退休的Dwight D. Eisenhower总统

463
00:35:43,076 --> 00:35:44,741
Thank you all very much.
非常感谢大家的配合

464
00:37:31,246 --> 00:37:34,673
Here we are, Norman's inner sanctum.
这就是，Norman的私密小空间

465
00:37:40,226 --> 00:37:41,692
Now, Hitch.
希胖

466
00:37:41,716 --> 00:37:46,201
Explain to me why I'm watching Marion undress?
能不能解释一下为什么我要看Marion脱衣服？

467
00:37:46,224 --> 00:37:48,044
I feel like I should take offense at that.
我觉得这应该算是冒犯我了

468
00:37:48,068 --> 00:37:51,005
Perhaps Norman secretly watched his mother
也许是因为Norman曾经偷看过她老妈

469
00:37:51,029 --> 00:37:54,233
preparing for her nightly bath.
准备每夜的沐浴

470
00:37:54,256 --> 00:37:57,168
Yes, maybe there was a transom over the bathroom door?
嗯对，或许浴室门上也有一个小窗户

471
00:37:57,191 --> 00:38:00,868
Yeah, which he could access by climbing on a chair,
没错，他可以站在一张椅子上就能偷窥到

472
00:38:00,891 --> 00:38:04,120
so long as he was stealthy.
只要他不发出任何声响

473
00:38:04,144 --> 00:38:07,748
A boy's first glimpse of a naked woman is usually his mother.
一个男生第一个见到的裸体女性往往就是通过偷窥母亲

474
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:12,067
So I'm reliving the past,
所以我还活在过去

475
00:38:12,068 --> 00:38:14,505
repeating a ritual with Marion?
在Marion身上重复这种仪式

476
00:38:14,528 --> 00:38:16,442
Don't ask me.
别问我

477
00:38:16,466 --> 00:38:21,363
I'm just a man hiding in the corner with my camera, watching.
我只是一个藏在角落的一台摄像机

478
00:38:21,387 --> 00:38:25,575
My camera will tell you the truth. The absolute truth.
摄像机才能告诉你和观众真正的真相

479
00:38:27,324 --> 00:38:29,168
Hitch, I have a question.
希胖，我有个问题

480
00:38:29,191 --> 00:38:32,480
Why is the hole so much larger on this side?
为什么这个洞在这一边要大些？

481
00:38:32,503 --> 00:38:35,187
All the better to see you with, my dear.
是为了更好地偷窥你啊

482
00:38:36,663 --> 00:38:39,477
At the greatest possible angle.
这样才能有更广的视角

483
00:39:04,100 --> 00:39:05,757
And cut!
好了！

484
00:39:24,153 --> 00:39:26,231
If you ask me, the credits should read
非要我说，我倒是觉得演职员名单上可以改成

485
00:39:26,254 --> 00:39:30,338
"Screenplay by Joseph Stefano and Alma Reville."
“编剧：Joseph Stefano、Alma Reville”

486
00:39:30,361 --> 00:39:32,840
The people who matter know.
两个在意的人

487
00:39:38,003 --> 00:39:41,340
Alma, you always know the answer. Is this really going to work?
我知道你慧眼独到。这真的能成么？

488
00:39:47,670 --> 00:39:49,953
See you tomorrow.
再说吧，明天见

489
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:05,394
Hello, stranger.
你好，路人甲

490
00:40:05,418 --> 00:40:09,434
- Whit! - Where have you been hiding?
- Whit！ - 最近怎么找不到你？

491
00:40:09,457 --> 00:40:11,512
Oh, God...!
噢上帝

492
00:40:11,524 --> 00:40:14,424
- I've been finishing the revisions on... - Psycho.
- 我刚刚修订完…… - 《惊魂记》我知道

493
00:40:14,448 --> 00:40:17,160
- Mm-hmm. - And how is the old boy?
- 你猜对了 - 阿希怎么样了？

494
00:40:17,182 --> 00:40:21,439
He is in a state of unbridled ecstasy now that he's back on the set.
他正处于回归拍摄的狂野躁动当中

495
00:40:21,463 --> 00:40:23,517
And you? How are you?
你呢？你怎么样？

496
00:40:24,609 --> 00:40:29,659
Well, two thousand words to do for Reader's Digest on
我最近还得赶的两千字的稿子给《读者文摘》

497
00:40:29,683 --> 00:40:33,018
what it's like to be married to a man obsessed by murder.
谁叫我跟一个爱凶杀的人结婚

498
00:40:35,918 --> 00:40:39,578
Alma, you deserve a break.
Alma，你应该休息一下了

499
00:40:40,603 --> 00:40:42,599
Let's drive up to Santa Barbara.
让我们开车到Santa Barbara去

500
00:40:42,622 --> 00:40:46,620
We'll have Emilio fry up those juicy steaks that we love so much at El Encanto.
到El Encanto吃点我们最喜欢的Emilio炸的多汁牛排

501
00:40:48,214 --> 00:40:50,794
Mr. Hitchcock, we're ready for you on the set.
希区柯克先生，我们都准备好了

502
00:40:55,096 --> 00:40:58,836
- Mr. Hitchcock. - I'll be there in a moment.
- 希区柯克先生 - 我一会儿就去

503
00:41:22,765 --> 00:41:25,228
Long line at the supermarket?
超市很多人么？

504
00:41:28,226 --> 00:41:30,894
No. Actually, I'm home earlier than I expected.
不会啊，我以为会更晚到家呢

505
00:41:34,510 --> 00:41:39,243
- Would you like a cocktail? - No, and you shouldn't have one either.
- 想喝杯鸡尾酒么？ - 不，你也不许喝

506
00:41:46,790 --> 00:41:50,684
- That hasn't been washed yet. - I don't care.
- 那还没洗呢 - 我不在乎

507
00:41:53,645 --> 00:41:58,102
Oh, I was filming all day today with John Gavin.
我和John Gavin一起拍了一整天了

508
00:41:58,126 --> 00:42:00,529
He's a good-looking chap.
他可帅了

509
00:42:00,544 --> 00:42:04,017
But really, plywood is more expressive.
但真的，plywood？的表现更抢眼

510
00:42:05,358 --> 00:42:07,916
I think his love scene with Janet Leigh
我觉得他和Janet Leigh的情爱戏

511
00:42:07,940 --> 00:42:11,693
may be most horrifying thing in the movie.
可能是全片最糟糕的一幕

512
00:42:15,333 --> 00:42:18,205
Even your friend Mr. Whitfield Cook
我想你的朋友Whitfield先生

513
00:42:18,206 --> 00:42:20,793
would be better in the scene.
演的还更好

514
00:42:22,249 --> 00:42:25,528
Why don't you tell him yourself? I'm sure he'd be very flattered.
你完全可以亲自告诉他，他会非常开心的

515
00:42:36,790 --> 00:42:39,244
You know, my dear,
亲爱的，

516
00:42:39,268 --> 00:42:44,681
maybe I was a bit too dismissive about your friend
可能我对你的好朋友太轻率了

517
00:42:44,698 --> 00:42:47,688
Whitfield's book.
我指的是他的那本书

518
00:42:48,885 --> 00:42:54,232
Perhaps he and Elizabeth could come over this weekend
也不知道这周末能不能邀请他和Elizabeth来这儿玩

519
00:42:54,255 --> 00:42:56,755
and walk me through it, as they say.
然后照他们的意思让我好好看看那本书

520
00:42:58,790 --> 00:43:01,654
Lovely woman, Elizabeth.
Elizabeth是个好女人

521
00:43:05,291 --> 00:43:10,054
I was hoping you could come to the set tomorrow.
我想让你来一趟片场

522
00:43:11,591 --> 00:43:15,012
Yes. Well, I'll see how my day shapes up.
好啊，我先看看明天有什么安排

523
00:43:16,002 --> 00:43:18,035
Yes.
好的

524
00:43:23,358 --> 00:43:27,491
You think you can get away with it, don't you? But you can't.
你以为你可以逃掉。可是你逃不掉

525
00:43:27,515 --> 00:43:30,229
You think they can't tell, but they can.
你以为它们不会出卖你，其实它们都会

526
00:43:30,253 --> 00:43:32,162
They know.
它们太明显了

527
00:43:32,186 --> 00:43:36,988
You can feel that noose tightening around that breakable little neck.
你完全可以感受到那紧绕脖子的绳索

528
00:43:37,006 --> 00:43:38,993
I mean, you could return the money secretly,
换句话说，你完全可以把钱悄悄还回去

529
00:43:39,017 --> 00:43:41,165
but what would that prove? It's too late.
但是那又有什么用？亡羊补牢了

530
00:43:41,189 --> 00:43:43,999
Marion Crane always so tight, so respectable,
Marion Crane做事总是特别紧凑、体面

531
00:43:44,023 --> 00:43:47,713
so prim and so proper and perfect. Untouchable unsullied Miss Crane.
拘谨、恰当、完美。高尚圣洁的Crane小姐。

532
00:43:47,737 --> 00:43:50,107
Daddy's perfect little angel.
爸爸的乖女儿

533
00:43:50,130 --> 00:43:55,080
Now they all know those dirty little secrets you've been hiding so long.
现在他们都知道了你那些隐藏已久的秘密

534
00:43:55,102 --> 00:43:57,151
Messy, sticky little lunchtime trysts
和一个叫Samuel Loomis“哎呀妈真帅”的失败男人

535
00:43:57,175 --> 00:44:01,458
with that oh-so-handsome failure Mr. Samuel Loomis.
纠缠、粘黏的午间秘密约会

536
00:44:01,481 --> 00:44:03,823
They'll smirk, they'll gossip, and they'll whisper.
他们偷笑，他们会八卦，他们会窃窃私语

537
00:44:03,846 --> 00:44:07,333
Even your boss, straight-laced, hatchet-faced Mr. George Lowery,
甚至你那个古板严肃的瘦脸George Lowery小老板

538
00:44:07,357 --> 00:44:12,538
why even he can smell the rancid, pungent scent of sex all over you.
为什么连他能嗅出你身上散发的刺鼻的性爱恶臭！？

539
00:44:13,880 --> 00:44:15,750
All right. Circle that and print it.
好了，把那卷到时候洗出来

540
00:44:15,768 --> 00:44:17,905
Let's get this thing fixed once and for all.
一次过就好了，而且争取所有的都顺利

541
00:44:17,928 --> 00:44:20,277
I'm sick and tired of it. Come on.
我烦死了快

542
00:44:22,145 --> 00:44:24,199
Why's it making that noise?
什么噪声？

543
00:44:24,223 --> 00:44:27,992
- When's it going to take to reset? - About five.
- 什么时候修好？ - 五点吧

544
00:44:35,770 --> 00:44:37,308
Come in.
门开着

545
00:44:38,858 --> 00:44:41,417
Thought you could use a little pick-me-up.
喝点提神的吧

546
00:44:41,441 --> 00:44:43,921
- Oh, you're so sweet. Thank you. - Not at all.
- 你人实在太好了，谢谢 - 不用

547
00:44:43,944 --> 00:44:46,707
- Here, have a seat. - Thanks.
- 来，坐下 - 谢谢

548
00:44:46,730 --> 00:44:50,546
I can't imagine your husband will be too pleased with what just happened.
你丈夫要是知道了刚才发生的事情应该会不乐意吧

549
00:44:50,563 --> 00:44:53,017
Well, you know.
嗯

550
00:44:53,040 --> 00:44:56,248
Tony and the kids, you'd be surprised what comes out of their mouths sometimes.
Tony和孩子们，有的时候他们说的话会让你大吃一惊

551
00:44:56,259 --> 00:44:58,370
That's true.
那倒是

552
00:44:59,207 --> 00:45:01,890
You haven't spoken to him much about your personal life, have you?
你也不太对他聊你自己的私人生活吧？

553
00:45:02,525 --> 00:45:05,475
Hitch? No, not really.
你是说希胖？是不会

554
00:45:07,349 --> 00:45:09,107
I'd keep it that way if I were you.
觉得你最好能够保持好这种距离

555
00:45:13,766 --> 00:45:14,950
Why?
怎么说？

556
00:45:15,878 --> 00:45:18,553
Well, it starts with him wanting to choose your hairstyle.
从他要求你应该有的发型那一刻开始

557
00:45:18,567 --> 00:45:20,539
Then he wants to choose your clothes,
接下来就是帮你挑衣服

558
00:45:20,563 --> 00:45:23,917
and your friends, and how many children you should have.
过滤朋友，最后甚至管到你应该生几个小孩儿

559
00:45:25,056 --> 00:45:30,084
You know that poor, tortured soul Jimmy Stewart played in Vertigo?
你知道《迷魂记》主角Jimmy Stewart有多惨么？

560
00:45:30,108 --> 00:45:32,503
That's Hitch...
他几乎成了第二个希胖

561
00:45:32,526 --> 00:45:35,091
Only younger, slimmer and better-looking.
只不过换了个好看的皮囊

562
00:45:35,115 --> 00:45:37,275
Oh, I don't know.
我不清楚

563
00:45:37,299 --> 00:45:39,577
Compared to Orson Welles, he's a sweetheart.
和奥逊威尔逊比起来，希胖算好的了

564
00:45:47,480 --> 00:45:51,403
See? He's always watching.
看。他总是在监视着每个人

565
00:46:31,415 --> 00:46:34,609
- Jack, how long is this going to take? - Just need five minutes.
- Jack，还需要多长时间才能准备好？ - 五分钟

566
00:46:34,632 --> 00:46:36,673
Let's get a move on it. We haven't got all day.
快点，时间不多了

567
00:46:36,685 --> 00:46:39,139
Why does it keep burning out all the time?
这玩意儿怎么总是会烧坏？

568
00:46:39,151 --> 00:46:43,070
- Get it fixed. What's the hold-up? - It's still engaged.
- 快点弄好。有人接么？ - 还是占线

569
00:46:44,092 --> 00:46:46,823
Hitch, I'm stuck on Lila's first scene.
希胖，我不看懂这第一场戏

570
00:46:46,846 --> 00:46:49,260
I don't know how strongly I should confront Sam and the detective...
我不知道对抗Sam和侦探的时候应该用什么情感？

571
00:46:49,283 --> 00:46:53,316
Darling, just fake it. Fake it. You know how to do that. Act.
亲爱的，就假装，假装懂么。不就是演戏么

572
00:46:53,340 --> 00:46:55,618
Where are my revisions?
修订后的剧本呢？

573
00:46:58,163 --> 00:47:01,666
Come on, does it really require two men to carry a light stand?
拜托，搬个灯架真的需要两个人么

574
00:47:01,689 --> 00:47:04,249
- Help them. - I'll take care of it right away, Mr. Hitchcock.
- 帮他们 - 就快好了希区柯克先生

575
00:47:04,270 --> 00:47:07,099
All the difference when the money's coming out of your own pocket, isn't it?
自己掏钱的就是不一样

576
00:47:07,100 --> 00:47:08,992
- We'll have a late lunch. - Right.
- 我们可以晚点吃午饭 - 好啊

577
00:47:09,016 --> 00:47:12,620
- I'll make the reservation for 1:30. - Oh, Whit.
- 我来订座，一点半 - 噢，Whit

578
00:47:12,644 --> 00:47:15,036
What would I do without you?
我要是没了你怎么办？

579
00:47:15,402 --> 00:47:18,733
- Till then, bye-bye. - Bye.
- 到时候再说，再见 - 再见

580
00:47:26,481 --> 00:47:29,136
Whit, what did you forget now?
Whit，你又忘了说什么了么？

581
00:47:31,049 --> 00:47:32,387
Whit?
Whit？

582
00:47:36,826 --> 00:47:38,229
Whit?
是你么？

583
00:48:00,739 --> 00:48:02,510
- Mr. Hitchcock, sir, please... - No, not now.
- 希区柯克先生，拜托了，希…… - 现在不行！

584
00:48:02,511 --> 00:48:04,159
Every press outlet is dying for photos.
每个报社都在求工作照

585
00:48:04,160 --> 00:48:05,761
If we could just get one photo, please!
哪怕是一张照片

586
00:48:05,762 --> 00:48:08,647
Get off my set! I'll have security... Get off my set!
滚出我的片场！不然我就叫保安了

587
00:48:08,670 --> 00:48:10,844
Just go! Get rid of this man. He's a bloody pest.
滚！谁帮我赶走这个男人，他是个害虫

588
00:48:10,867 --> 00:48:12,800
Get him off the set now!
让他滚，马上！

589
00:48:12,823 --> 00:48:15,263
- Are you okay? You've gone very pale. - I tell you get away.
- 你还好么？你看起来气色很差 - 我已经告诉你走开了

590
00:48:15,287 --> 00:48:17,914
Stop following me around like a puppy dog and get me a drink.
别像个跟屁虫一样，去给我弄杯酒

591
00:48:17,938 --> 00:48:21,098
- It's not even 3:00... - Now give me the key to the cabinets.
- 现在连三点都还没到…… - 给我储藏柜的钥匙

592
00:48:24,823 --> 00:48:28,357
Hello, Hitch. How's the picture?
你好希胖，拍的怎么样了？

593
00:48:28,380 --> 00:48:30,165
I'm hearing interesting things.
我听到一些有趣的消息

594
00:48:30,189 --> 00:48:32,220
It's a miracle anyone can hear anything
听到的东西总是难得的

595
00:48:32,244 --> 00:48:35,340
above the noise coming from Geoffrey Shurlock's office.
还是从Geoffrey Shurlock办公室噪声中听到的

596
00:48:35,364 --> 00:48:38,569
You know, I shouldn't be in a position of just hearing things, Hitch.
你也知道，我不能光听啊

597
00:48:38,593 --> 00:48:41,814
- It's time you showed me some footage. - Why?
- 总该该给我看看一些片段吧 - 为什么？

598
00:48:41,838 --> 00:48:45,114
To see if you're making a picture Paramount can actually release.
看看派拉蒙适不适合发行

599
00:48:45,137 --> 00:48:50,117
As you well know, my contract guarantees me final cut.
你应该知道，签约合同里写明了我有最终剪辑权

600
00:48:50,125 --> 00:48:51,954
Your contract also says
可合同里也写了

601
00:48:51,977 --> 00:48:54,255
Paramount isn't required to distribute any film
派拉蒙有权不发行你任何

602
00:48:54,267 --> 00:48:55,793
that could cause us embarrassment.
给我们带来难堪的电影

603
00:48:55,817 --> 00:48:59,796
Unlike the last five Martin and Lewis films you're all so proud of.
反正我的电影不像你引以为豪的五部Martin&Lewis大电影

604
00:48:59,820 --> 00:49:02,661
I demand to see some footage. Hitch!
我命令你给我片段

605
00:49:02,684 --> 00:49:06,637
You show me some damn footage now! Hitch!
我命令你给我看你的该死的片段！

606
00:49:24,464 --> 00:49:28,230
You have no idea how wonderful it is not to have to look after someone.
不当保姆的感觉真好

607
00:49:28,254 --> 00:49:31,436
I mean, even if it's just for two hours.
哪怕只不当两个小时

608
00:49:31,459 --> 00:49:35,088
So where are we going, Whit? You haven't told me.
我们去哪儿啊，Whit？你还没告诉我呢

609
00:49:35,111 --> 00:49:39,103
- I have a little surprise. - Ooh!
- 给你一个惊喜 - 噢我喜欢

610
00:49:49,339 --> 00:49:54,435
- Where's your driver? - I've been asking myself the same thing.
- 你的司机呢？ - 我也想知道

611
00:49:54,459 --> 00:49:56,936
Well, I can give you a ride if you'd like.
我送你一程吧

612
00:49:57,967 --> 00:50:01,055
Oh, my God. What a tiny car.
这车也太小了

613
00:50:01,078 --> 00:50:03,511
What are these things? I keep looking at them.
这是什么，我盯着看了好久

614
00:50:03,512 --> 00:50:06,439
- Candy corn. The girls love them. - Candy corn?
- 糖玉米。女孩儿们很喜欢 - 糖玉米啊

615
00:50:06,462 --> 00:50:09,016
I nicked them from Tony's dressing room.
我从Tony更衣室里偷偷顺出来的

616
00:50:09,027 --> 00:50:12,709
Oh. Very nice.
真好吃

617
00:50:12,732 --> 00:50:15,804
I thought you only ate those Fauchon chocolates.
我以为你只吃Fauchon巧克力

618
00:50:15,818 --> 00:50:19,094
Needs must when the devil drives, my dear.
谁叫魔鬼把这东西摆在我面前

619
00:50:20,128 --> 00:50:26,038
- Oh, luckily I'm driving. - Thank God for that.
- 还好是我不是魔鬼（Drive的双关） - 谢天谢地

620
00:50:26,061 --> 00:50:28,897
He's always had obsessions with his leading ladies.
他总是对他电影里的女主角有感觉

621
00:50:28,898 --> 00:50:32,944
Just that this time it feels like he's using them against me.
唯独这次感觉像是特地针对我

622
00:50:32,958 --> 00:50:35,499
Well I suppose he's like any great artist.
我觉得他就和其他伟大的艺术家一样

623
00:50:35,500 --> 00:50:38,539
Impossible to live with, but worth the effort.
没法生活在一起，不过尝试一下价值颇丰

624
00:50:38,562 --> 00:50:41,666
Did you know before we got together, I was his boss?
你知道我们在一起之前，我可是他的老板呢？

625
00:50:41,667 --> 00:50:45,229
He had to work his way up to assistant director before he dared ask me out.
他当上了导演助理才敢约我

626
00:50:45,245 --> 00:50:46,771
- Really? Huh! - Mm-hmm.
- 真的假的？ - 真的

627
00:50:52,002 --> 00:50:53,864
See that house over there?
看到那座房子了么？

628
00:50:55,116 --> 00:50:57,688
- Yes. - What do you think of it?
- 看到了 - 你觉得怎么样？

629
00:50:57,711 --> 00:51:02,131
- Lovely, isn't it. What a great position. - It's mine.
- 位置不错啊 - 那是我的房子

630
00:51:02,154 --> 00:51:04,315
I just talked to Elizabeth. She didn't say anything about it.
我才和Elizabeth聊过天，她从没提起过有过这房子

631
00:51:04,338 --> 00:51:07,836
She doesn't know anything about it. Nobody does.
她从来不知道这房子。没人知道

632
00:51:07,859 --> 00:51:09,514
Want to see it?
参观一下？

633
00:51:21,697 --> 00:51:24,535
- Thank you, my dear. - Any time.
- 谢谢，亲爱的 - 随时效劳

634
00:51:24,550 --> 00:51:26,529
- Can I keep these? - Absolutely.
- 这个我能拿走么？ - 完全可以

635
00:51:26,553 --> 00:51:28,601
- Would you like one? - No thank you.
- 再给你一颗吧？ - 不用了谢谢

636
00:51:28,622 --> 00:51:30,102
- All right. Well, thank you. - Hitch?
- 那好吧，再次谢谢你 - 希胖？

637
00:51:30,125 --> 00:51:31,440
What?
怎么了？

638
00:51:33,002 --> 00:51:36,627
What really did happen with you and Vera?
你和Vera之间发生了什么事？

639
00:51:37,776 --> 00:51:40,288
Oh. Vera.
噢，Vera啊

640
00:51:42,179 --> 00:51:45,805
She was going to play the lead in Vertigo.
她本来要演《迷魂记》里的女主角

641
00:51:45,824 --> 00:51:50,212
Two weeks before filming she told me was pregnant.
开拍两周前她告诉我她怀孕了

642
00:51:51,317 --> 00:51:54,393
I was going to make her into a star.
我本来可以把她捧红的

643
00:51:54,416 --> 00:51:58,539
But she chose the life of a housewife instead.
但是她还是选择做家庭主妇

644
00:52:02,642 --> 00:52:05,549
Why do they do it, I wonder?
我不明白女人为什么那么善变

645
00:52:06,364 --> 00:52:09,174
Why do they always betray me?
为什么她们总要背叛我

646
00:52:13,696 --> 00:52:17,212
Oh, very Bohemian.
哇，很波西米亚风格嘛

647
00:52:17,235 --> 00:52:20,291
I just leased it for the off season.
租这套房子无非是图个清静

648
00:52:20,292 --> 00:52:24,860
A place to get away from the wife, and kids, and writing.
一个没有妻子、孩子还有写作的地方

649
00:52:32,115 --> 00:52:35,324
Whit, I hope you don't have the wrong idea.
Whit，我不希望你想歪了

650
00:52:37,121 --> 00:52:42,125
If you were serious about helping me adapt my book,
如果你想要认真帮我改编我的书

651
00:52:42,148 --> 00:52:45,082
I thought it might make the perfect...
我真心觉得这个地方

652
00:52:46,809 --> 00:52:48,709
hideaway.
再也合适不过了

653
00:53:01,996 --> 00:53:05,272
Relax! Naughty boys, calm down.
乖大头乖

654
00:55:49,448 --> 00:55:52,195
Oh, by the way, I forgot to tell you
噢，我差点忘记告诉你

655
00:55:52,219 --> 00:55:55,503
I read your treatment of that story.
我了你对那个故事的改编

656
00:55:56,761 --> 00:55:59,428
Taxi to... Where was it, dear?
“去往什么的出租车”啊？

657
00:55:59,429 --> 00:56:03,052
- Dubrovnik. - That's it. Dubrovnik.
- “去往Dubrovnik” - 对就是这个，Dubrovnik

658
00:56:06,457 --> 00:56:10,677
- Would you care to hear my opinion? - Well, yes, naturally.
- 你想听听我的建议么？ - 当然了当然了

659
00:56:12,383 --> 00:56:14,102
Right, then.
那好

660
00:56:16,013 --> 00:56:19,578
Well, my dear, there's no other way of saying it, is there?
嗯，怎么说好呢，不过也没什么其他的表达方式了

661
00:56:19,579 --> 00:56:21,953
It's a stillborn.
有种要死的感觉

662
00:56:26,895 --> 00:56:28,703
How so?
怎么说？

663
00:56:28,726 --> 00:56:31,289
First of all, the plot's a bit of a muddle, isn't it?
首先，剧情就有点混乱

664
00:56:32,252 --> 00:56:34,214
Some of those jokes are awfully like the ones
有些玩笑话也太像

665
00:56:34,238 --> 00:56:36,646
we did so much better hundreds of years ago
我几百年前就已经在

666
00:56:36,668 --> 00:56:38,918
in The Lady Vanishes.
《贵妇失踪记》里玩烂的了

667
00:56:38,937 --> 00:56:43,827
Also your villain is rather weak. Well he's very weak, in fact.
而且你们的反派也太弱了。实话说，是弱爆了

668
00:56:44,882 --> 00:56:46,785
But I think the big failure
但是我觉得最大的失败就在于

669
00:56:46,808 --> 00:56:52,443
is the relationship between the heroine and the hero, you see.
男女主人公之间的感情关系，你觉得呢？

670
00:56:55,352 --> 00:56:59,203
Probably if you weren't so smitten with your friend Whitfield Cook,
可能如果你没跟Whitfield Cook走那么近

671
00:56:59,226 --> 00:57:02,318
you'd be able to see that, wouldn't you?
也许你看的更清楚，不是么？

672
00:57:06,576 --> 00:57:07,668
But then I suppose
当然了，我也知道

673
00:57:07,691 --> 00:57:13,345
women never really care to face the truth when their hearts are involved, do they?
女人们一但将心投入进去之后很难再让她们回头了不是么？

674
00:57:15,330 --> 00:57:19,229
How would you know what really goes on between a man and a woman?
你哪知道什么男人和女人之间的事情

675
00:57:35,348 --> 00:57:38,177
My God, what a bloody mess.
我的天啊，这也太脏了

676
00:58:29,779 --> 00:58:31,494
- No! - Ah!
- 别！ - 啊！

677
00:58:31,513 --> 00:58:33,796
More! More!
强烈一点！强烈一点！

678
00:58:33,816 --> 00:58:35,960
- No! Oh! - Use some guts!
- 不要！啊！ - 再凶狠点

679
00:58:35,977 --> 00:58:37,938
- Come on! No! - Oh!
- 扎凶一点！ - 啊！

680
00:58:37,962 --> 00:58:41,043
- More anger! - Oh! Oh!
- 愤怒点 - 啊啊

681
00:58:41,066 --> 00:58:43,265
All right, cut! Cut! Cut!
别拍了

682
00:58:43,266 --> 00:58:44,737
For God's sake!
我的妈呀

683
00:58:44,738 --> 00:58:47,460
Will someone get me a proper stunt double?
谁能帮我找个靠谱点的凶手替身啊？

684
00:58:47,473 --> 00:58:50,091
Now give me the knife! Not yet!
把刀给我！情绪还不对！

685
00:58:52,327 --> 00:58:55,311
Ungovernable rage!
给我无法控制的情绪！

686
00:58:57,248 --> 00:59:00,388
Homicidal violence!
这是杀人狂一般的暴力！

687
00:59:23,854 --> 00:59:26,804
Cut! Cut and print!
好了。洗出来吧

688
00:59:30,649 --> 00:59:32,468
We've got it.
搞好了

689
00:59:55,139 --> 00:59:57,898
Oh, not now, Ed.
Ed，这个时候别闹我

690
00:59:57,921 --> 01:00:00,997
It's really not the time.
时候不对

691
01:00:07,938 --> 01:00:11,491
You just can't keep this stuff bottled up.
你根本没法平息你的怒气

692
01:00:26,038 --> 01:00:29,079
Oh, God! Hitch, Hitch, you all right?
希胖，你还好么？

693
01:00:29,808 --> 01:00:32,506
- Can you hear me? - Alma...
- 你能听到我说话么？ - Alma……

694
01:00:34,550 --> 01:00:39,593
What if Bridget and Constantine get into the cab at the same time?
如果让男主角和女主角在同一辆出租车里呢？

695
01:00:39,617 --> 01:00:42,658
Now what if they try and get in at exactly the same time?
那如果他们俩刚刚好同时进出租呢？

696
01:00:42,682 --> 01:00:45,176
- Yes. What do you mean, "exactly"?
- 嗯，什么是“刚刚好”？

697
01:00:45,200 --> 01:00:49,921
I mean they both reach for the cab door at exactly the same time.
我的意思是他们俩同时碰到车门

698
01:00:49,922 --> 01:00:51,587
- They quickly touch. - Yes.
- 他们瞬间触碰到对方 - 好

699
01:00:51,611 --> 01:00:55,075
We start on the hands, we pan up to the eyes, and...
镜头先是给到他们俩的手，镜头升起，到它们的眼睛

700
01:00:55,098 --> 01:00:57,897
Oh, that feels better already.
非常棒

701
01:01:00,954 --> 01:01:03,373
- Are you going to get that? - What?
- 你不接电话了么？ - 什么？

702
01:01:29,679 --> 01:01:31,639
Listen, I've told Peggy
听着，我已经告诉Peggy了

703
01:01:31,663 --> 01:01:35,323
you have to get this sequence shot today.
今天要给我拍好这个长镜头

704
01:01:35,346 --> 01:01:36,579
What's the hold-up?
有什么问题？

705
01:01:36,603 --> 01:01:38,728
We tried it ten different ways and it looks terrible.
我们拍了十次，都太糟糕了

706
01:01:38,745 --> 01:01:45,483
No, it has to be a high angle. You'll tip off the big surprise.
必须得用大角度摄影，这样才能显出惊讶

707
01:01:45,508 --> 01:01:47,347
Just get the process shot.
反正就是全程摄影

708
01:01:47,675 --> 01:01:51,096
How can he hold on to the camera frame if he's waving his arms?
如果他要挥手，那到底怎么拿稳摄像机啊？

709
01:01:52,101 --> 01:01:55,566
Why don't you just push all the gas from the top of the stairs?
你就把所以气体从楼梯最上面一层喷出来嘛

710
01:01:57,326 --> 01:01:58,864
No one's going to get hurt.
不会有人因此受伤的

711
01:01:58,876 --> 01:02:00,686
What bloody idiots they are.
这群笨蛋

712
01:02:01,872 --> 01:02:03,791
- What are you doing? - No more phone calls.
- 你这是干嘛？ - 不许再打电话了

713
01:02:03,815 --> 01:02:06,269
- Oh, but... - You're burning up.
- 可是 - 你不能再逼自己了

714
01:02:06,292 --> 01:02:09,019
Burning off our money, that's what we're doing.
你这是在浪费我们的资金

715
01:02:09,042 --> 01:02:12,095
We're two days behind and I'm stuck in this bloody bed.
进度已经延迟两天了，而我还在这儿躺着

716
01:02:12,118 --> 01:02:14,106
- Where do you think you're going? - I've got to go to the set.
- 你以为你能去哪？ - 我必须去片场

717
01:02:14,127 --> 01:02:19,071
- We can't lose another day. - You stay in bed. I'll deal with it.
- 我们不能再延迟一天啊 - 你给我躺着，我去帮你处理

718
01:02:19,094 --> 01:02:23,067
I'd hate to take you away from your writing partner.
我才不想把你从你的绯闻男友那儿拽回来

719
01:02:24,206 --> 01:02:26,847
You stay under the blankets, Alfred.
你好好给我躺着，艾弗

720
01:02:32,026 --> 01:02:33,263
- Mrs. Hitchcock. - Good morning.
- 希区柯克夫人你好 - 早上好

721
01:02:33,286 --> 01:02:35,285
Where's Mr. Hitchcock?
希胖大人呢

722
01:02:40,727 --> 01:02:43,193
Don't stop work because of me.
不要因为我来了你们就不工作了

723
01:02:43,216 --> 01:02:46,869
I'm only here as one of the two people paying your salaries.
我无非是管财务的

724
01:02:46,892 --> 01:02:49,578
- What's the scene number? - 173.
- 拍到第几场了？ - 第173

725
01:02:50,978 --> 01:02:52,444
Storyboards?
故事板在哪儿

726
01:02:56,372 --> 01:02:59,097
All right. Put Martin in the chair. Turn the camera around to face him.
那好。Martin坐好在椅子上，让摄像机对着他

727
01:02:59,098 --> 01:03:02,096
We'll shoot the fall against a rear screen.
我们来拍这后银幕下的摔倒

728
01:03:02,111 --> 01:03:05,134
And, Jack, that len should be a 35mm.
那个镜头要用35毫米的（我感觉这里英字错了）

729
01:03:07,215 --> 01:03:10,066
Now, David, you know how Paramount loves Jerry Lewis,
你看，David，你也知道我们派拉蒙确实很喜欢Jerry Lewis的风格

730
01:03:10,078 --> 01:03:11,787
but this one is right up your alley, and I would consider...
可问题是这可是你已经驾轻就熟的题材，而且我是这样想的……

731
01:03:11,799 --> 01:03:13,607
Barney?
Barney？

732
01:03:13,618 --> 01:03:15,297
Alma!
Alma！

733
01:03:15,320 --> 01:03:16,953
You know David Kirkpatrick.
你也认识David Kirkpatrick

734
01:03:16,970 --> 01:03:18,156
- Hello. - Hello.
你好

735
01:03:18,179 --> 01:03:20,510
He's working on Jerry Lewis developing a new picture.
他正在帮Jerry Lewis做新电影

736
01:03:20,533 --> 01:03:22,878
So he's free to help if you need.
如果有用到他的地方他完全没问题

737
01:03:24,158 --> 01:03:25,520
That won't be necessary.
没这个必要了

738
01:03:25,543 --> 01:03:29,378
- But you're nearly three days behind. - Yes. Well, we can manage.
- 但是你已经落后进度三天了 - 没错，不过我们可以补救回来

739
01:03:29,402 --> 01:03:32,715
Alma, we both know what kind of film this is.
Alma，我们都知道这是一部什么电影

740
01:03:32,739 --> 01:03:36,066
The smart thing to do would be to help Hitch finish it.
最适当的举措就是帮希胖完成它

741
01:03:36,085 --> 01:03:37,711
Thank you for your concern, Barney.
谢谢你的关心，Barney

742
01:03:37,735 --> 01:03:41,383
But on a Hitchcock picture, there is only one director.
问题是这是希区柯克电影，导演只能是希区柯克

743
01:03:51,953 --> 01:03:53,870
No need to gawp.
都傻愣着干嘛呢

744
01:04:00,676 --> 01:04:03,276
You forgot to look in the bathroom.
你忘记去检查一下厕所

745
01:04:07,472 --> 01:04:11,111
A man like you missing a vital clue like that...
一个像你这样的人，如果丢掉一条重要的线索……

746
01:04:13,455 --> 01:04:15,315
What do you mean?
你想说什么？

747
01:04:18,726 --> 01:04:21,674
My mother always said
我妈说得好

748
01:04:22,642 --> 01:04:24,986
"If you want to do a job,
“精益求精”

749
01:04:26,937 --> 01:04:28,896
do it right."

750
01:04:41,878 --> 01:04:44,336
Check the floor.
来看一下地面

751
01:04:47,709 --> 01:04:49,543
Closer.
仔细点看

752
01:05:04,913 --> 01:05:08,264
You still think they're just writing together?
你还觉得他们俩只是“在一起写作”么

753
01:05:11,628 --> 01:05:14,257
What are you gonna do about it?
你下一步应该怎么做？

754
01:05:30,599 --> 01:05:32,402
Oh, Mrs. Hitchcock.
希区柯克夫人！

755
01:05:33,441 --> 01:05:37,051
I know Hitch isn't feeling very well, so I got him a little something.
我知道希胖最近身体抱恙，所以我给他准备了点东西

756
01:05:37,066 --> 01:05:39,918
Oh, how kind. Thank you very much.
你人太好了，谢谢你

757
01:05:40,699 --> 01:05:42,732
Candy corn.
糖玉米

758
01:05:42,756 --> 01:05:45,644
Well, he's always been very considerate of me.
他一直很照顾我

759
01:05:45,668 --> 01:05:48,024
I haven't always had that from my directors.
其他导演一般都没这么贴心

760
01:05:50,114 --> 01:05:53,310
Janet, I'd just like to say that
Janet，我想说

761
01:05:54,670 --> 01:05:56,920
you've been very professional.
以表现的非常敬业

762
01:05:58,179 --> 01:06:00,520
It hasn't gone unappreciated.
效果也非常好

763
01:06:01,766 --> 01:06:03,359
Thank you.
谢谢

764
01:06:03,382 --> 01:06:05,662
- Lovely seeing you. - You, too.
- 见到你还是很高兴的 - 我也是

765
01:06:25,753 --> 01:06:27,867
May I turn it down?
请问我能关小声点么？

766
01:06:35,931 --> 01:06:39,691
Well you'll be pleased to know that order has been restored.
你应该会很高兴我们片场的话事权已经捍卫下来了

767
01:06:41,668 --> 01:06:43,622
And a "thank you" would be nice.
你总可以说句“谢谢”吧

768
01:06:43,640 --> 01:06:47,170
We're still two days behind and $60,000 over budget.
可我们还是落后了两天，超支了六万

769
01:06:47,190 --> 01:06:50,442
Yes, well I'll cancel the wrap party. That'll save us $2000 right there.
那咱们就不开庆功宴了，这下就多了两千块

770
01:06:50,466 --> 01:06:54,626
And you won't be tempted by any champagne and cake.
正好你也不用馋着要香槟和蛋糕了

771
01:06:54,627 --> 01:06:57,730
Beware, all men are potential murderers.
你小心点，狗急了会跳墙的

772
01:06:59,622 --> 01:07:01,786
And for good reason.
而且还有正当理由

773
01:07:01,810 --> 01:07:04,610
All right, what's this all about?
够了！你到底在生气什么？

774
01:07:16,370 --> 01:07:18,902
Spending a lot of time at the beach?
去海滩这件事你怎么解释？

775
01:07:23,555 --> 01:07:27,701
Yes. Yes, it's where Whit and I are writing. He's rented a place.
没错，海滩上Whit租了座房子，我们俩一起写作

776
01:07:27,702 --> 01:07:31,235
Hardly the ideal situation to avoid distractions.
我想不会是个集中注意力写作的好地方吧

777
01:07:31,236 --> 01:07:34,388
Actually, it's very conducive to creative collaboration.
实际上，这对两个人合作非常有帮助

778
01:07:34,389 --> 01:07:36,890
I've already told you that treatment is a waste of time.
我已经告诉你了，修改它是浪费时间

779
01:07:36,913 --> 01:07:39,795
Well, didn't they say the same thing about Psycho?
你对《惊魂记》不也是这么说的么？

780
01:07:45,480 --> 01:07:48,205
Are you and Whit having an affair?
你和Whit在恋爱么？

781
01:07:55,198 --> 01:07:57,347
Oh, don't be absurd.
别想太多了

782
01:07:57,371 --> 01:08:01,609
He's working on something new. He just needs a little help, that's all.
他在捣鼓些新的作品，他无非是想要点帮忙

783
01:08:01,632 --> 01:08:04,455
Oh, what a coincidence. I'm working on something new
那太巧了，我也在捣鼓新作品

784
01:08:04,456 --> 01:08:06,041
and I could use a little help, too!
我也想要点帮忙

785
01:08:06,064 --> 01:08:07,411
Well, what do you think I've been doing?
你以为我之前在干嘛？

786
01:08:07,422 --> 01:08:09,465
Why are you spending all the hours of day and night with that
告诉我你为什么要和那个毫无才华的小屁孩

787
01:08:09,489 --> 01:08:12,125
talentless mummy's boy?
花上一整天时间？

788
01:08:13,118 --> 01:08:14,585
Because it's fun!
因为那会让我比较开心

789
01:08:14,609 --> 01:08:17,658
I am under extraordinary pressures on this picture,
这部电影让我倍感压力

790
01:08:17,682 --> 01:08:21,640
and the least you could do is give me your full support.
至少你也应该全力支持我

791
01:08:21,664 --> 01:08:24,857
Full support?
“全力支持”？

792
01:08:24,881 --> 01:08:27,286
We've mortgaged our house.
我们连房子都抵押了！

793
01:08:28,666 --> 01:08:30,333
Might I remind you
让我提醒你一下

794
01:08:30,357 --> 01:08:33,062
I have weighed in on every aspect of this film so far,
我在这电影里参与了每一个部分

795
01:08:33,086 --> 01:08:36,835
as I have done on every film you've made in the last three decades.
如同我在过去三十年你的每一部电影里的付出

796
01:08:36,859 --> 01:08:40,595
First time you show the film, it will be my notes that you want.
首映完了之后，我给你你想要的想法

797
01:08:40,618 --> 01:08:42,837
I celebrate with you when the reviews are good.
评论大好是我陪你庆祝

798
01:08:42,860 --> 01:08:44,468
I cry for you when they are bad.
评论差了我为你哭泣

799
01:08:44,491 --> 01:08:48,002
I host your parties and I put up with those fantasy romances
我主持你的派对，还要容忍你和你的那些女主角们的

800
01:08:48,025 --> 01:08:50,346
with your leading ladies.
奇妙关系

801
01:08:50,347 --> 01:08:52,623
And when you're out promoting this film around the world,
然后还有当你到世界各地宣传你的电影

802
01:08:52,624 --> 01:08:55,031
I will be there beside you, or rather, slightly behind you,
我要么一直陪伴着你，或者在你身后

803
01:08:55,054 --> 01:08:59,396
smiling endlessly for the press even though I'm ready to drop,
对媒体摆着笑容，哪怕我都快要流泪了

804
01:08:59,419 --> 01:09:03,095
and being gracious to people who look through me as if I were invisible
还要对那些当我不存在的人假装和善

805
01:09:03,096 --> 01:09:05,399
or elbow me aside because all they can see
而且他们还把我推到一边，因为他们眼里只有

806
01:09:05,400 --> 01:09:09,326
is the great and glorious genius Alfred Hitchcock!
伟大和荣耀的阿弗莱德・希区柯克

807
01:09:09,348 --> 01:09:13,366
And now, for the first time in years,
然而现在，这几年我第一次斗胆

808
01:09:13,367 --> 01:09:17,517
I dare to work on something that isn't an Alfred Hitchcock production
去做些“希区柯克电影”以外的作品

809
01:09:17,518 --> 01:09:20,835
and I'm met with accusation and criticisms?
却要遭到指控和非议？

810
01:09:22,379 --> 01:09:26,429
The work I am doing with Whit gives me pleasure and purpose,
我和Whit一起创作的作品让我愉快和有目标

811
01:09:26,430 --> 01:09:30,000
and it takes absolutely nothing away from you.
而且我不从你这索取任何东西

812
01:09:31,368 --> 01:09:35,664
Consider this a reminder: I am your wife, Alma Reville.
你给我记住了：我是你老婆，Alma Reville

813
01:09:35,687 --> 01:09:38,550
Not one of those contract blondes you badger
不是你合约下纠缠不清的妞

814
01:09:38,573 --> 01:09:41,732
and torment with your oh-so-specific directions.
也不是受控你“特别”导演法的玩偶

815
01:10:15,998 --> 01:10:17,681
Well...
嗯

816
01:10:17,694 --> 01:10:19,812
I guess this is goodbye.
我想也该说再见了

817
01:10:23,178 --> 01:10:25,632
Why didn't you stay with me?
你为什么不和我合作了

818
01:10:27,308 --> 01:10:31,617
I would have made you as big a star as Grace Kelly.
我可以把你捧得像Grace Kelly那样红的

819
01:10:35,270 --> 01:10:38,999
Well, unlike Grace Kelly, I can pick my own dry cleaning.
要是像她，我连自己去洗衣店都不行

820
01:10:39,603 --> 01:10:42,286
I've got a family, Hitch. A home.
我有一个家庭，希胖，一个家

821
01:10:45,366 --> 01:10:49,187
That blonde woman of mystery you're always after?
那个你一直想塑造的“金发女郎”形象

822
01:10:49,210 --> 01:10:51,159
She's a fantasy.
那只是一个梦

823
01:10:51,183 --> 01:10:52,852
She doesn't exist.
是不存在的

824
01:10:54,523 --> 01:10:57,871
There was a time when I thought I understood you.
我曾经以为我已经理解你了

825
01:10:59,404 --> 01:11:01,687
Understood women.
理解所有的女人了

826
01:11:53,172 --> 01:11:56,318
Alma, I thought you were coming later this afternoon.
Alma，我以为你下午会晚点来

827
01:11:56,342 --> 01:11:58,091
I thought you rented this place so we could write.
我以为你租这房子是为了写作

828
01:11:58,115 --> 01:11:59,841
I did.
还是啊

829
01:12:01,375 --> 01:12:05,542
- You're not going to say anything, are you? - Don't worry. I won't tell Elizabeth.
- 你不会对谁说吧 - 不要怕，我不会告诉Elizabeth的

830
01:12:05,550 --> 01:12:08,094
I mean to Hitch.
我指的是对Hitch

831
01:12:09,415 --> 01:12:14,699
Alma, we can't all be geniuses.
Alma，我们不可能全是天才

832
01:12:14,723 --> 01:12:16,801
You're incredibly talented.
只有你的才华如此

833
01:12:16,824 --> 01:12:19,917
But, after all, we want him to read the script with an open mind.
不过到最后，我们还是希望他能够有一个更宽容地看这个剧本

834
01:12:19,940 --> 01:12:21,197
Don't we?
我们？

835
01:12:22,500 --> 01:12:24,766
I wouldn't worry about that, Whit.
我不会再操心这件事了

836
01:12:29,689 --> 01:12:32,307
Sheriff, please, I'm worried.
警长大人，我担心的是

837
01:12:32,331 --> 01:12:35,419
Arbogast said he'd call as soon as he spoke with Mrs. Bates.
Arbogast说他跟Bates夫人说了后会给我们打电话

838
01:12:35,431 --> 01:12:37,485
That was yesterday evening.
那已经是昨天晚上了

839
01:12:37,509 --> 01:12:41,546
- Norman isn't married. - He said it was his mother.
- Norman可没有结婚 - 他说那是他的母亲

840
01:12:41,569 --> 01:12:45,366
Your detective saw Norman's mother up at the motel?
你雇的侦探说他在汽车旅店里看到Norman的母亲？

841
01:12:45,389 --> 01:12:47,139
In the upstairs window.
而且她在二楼的窗户旁

842
01:12:47,150 --> 01:12:49,582
He rang me right after she called out to him.
他从母亲那儿回来后就马上打电话给我了

843
01:12:49,606 --> 01:12:53,740
Missy, I think your detective must be a few cups in.
小姐，我想你的侦探是喝多了吧

844
01:12:53,764 --> 01:13:00,024
Mrs. Bates died of strychnine poisoning more than ten years ago.
Bates夫人十多年前就已经死于士的宁中毒了

845
01:13:00,047 --> 01:13:03,488
- Are you sure? - That body was...
- 你说的是真的么？ - 夫人当时的尸体……

846
01:13:09,984 --> 01:13:13,307
This is my favorite place.
这是我最喜欢的地方

847
01:13:13,330 --> 01:13:18,987
I just shut the door and make the world go away.
我只需要把门关上就可以让整个世界和我无关

848
01:13:19,844 --> 01:13:23,419
Don't you ever get lonely out here?
在这儿你从来都不孤独的么？

849
01:13:24,800 --> 01:13:27,989
I can always talk to my mother.
我可以和我妈说话

850
01:13:39,769 --> 01:13:42,528
That's strange.
奇怪

851
01:13:42,552 --> 01:13:45,823
Jesus Christ. I think we found his hiding place.
我的天啊，我想我们发现了他藏身之处

852
01:13:52,263 --> 01:13:54,747
That's my mother's room.
那是我妈的房间

853
01:13:55,598 --> 01:13:57,565
That's my mother's room.

854
01:14:04,365 --> 01:14:06,719
You can't go in there!
你们不能进去！

855
01:14:06,737 --> 01:14:08,778
Don't go in my mother's room!
不许进！

856
01:14:22,854 --> 01:14:25,203
Hitch?
希胖！

857
01:14:25,226 --> 01:14:27,152
Hitch?
希胖

858
01:14:28,244 --> 01:14:30,645
So what's the verdict?
审核如何？

859
01:14:30,669 --> 01:14:34,755
Let's just say it was a four-letter review and it wasn't "good."
他们只有一个字，这个字跟“好”没关系

860
01:14:37,212 --> 01:14:38,550
Screw him.
管他的

861
01:14:38,574 --> 01:14:42,082
It's too late for Paramount to back out, no matter what Balaban says.
管他Balaban说什么，派拉蒙这个时候已经没退路了

862
01:14:44,191 --> 01:14:49,009
The other route is to re-cut it as a two-parter for the TV series.
还有一条路，就是重新剪成两集投放到电视

863
01:14:49,031 --> 01:14:51,299
Because of the budget and the Hitchcock name,
顾及到预算还有希区柯克的金字招牌

864
01:14:51,311 --> 01:14:53,401
we stand a good chance of breaking even.
这是一个收回成本的好办法

865
01:14:55,667 --> 01:15:00,324
Look, I made Jimmy Stewart a millionaire on Winchester 73,
我用《百战宝枪》让Jimmy Stewart成为百万富翁

866
01:15:00,347 --> 01:15:01,744
and that was a dog.
而且那电影还不怎么地

867
01:15:01,768 --> 01:15:04,676
At least I could sit through your picture.
这部电影我起码看完了

868
01:15:07,508 --> 01:15:10,982
More importantly, what does Alma think?
不过更重要的，还是要先听听Alma的意见

869
01:15:35,383 --> 01:15:37,250
I was afraid you'd try to blame yourself.
我害怕你会责怪你自己

870
01:15:37,274 --> 01:15:38,577
I'm not talking of blame.
我不是责怪

871
01:15:38,589 --> 01:15:41,031
Leigh, how can you make plans if you're still not sure?
Leigh，你怎么能在你还没想清楚时就做决定

872
01:16:00,958 --> 01:16:03,751
Whit must've enjoyed writing for Colbert.
Whit能为Colbert写戏应该很开心吧

873
01:16:10,393 --> 01:16:12,960
How was the beach?
海滩那儿如何？

874
01:16:14,643 --> 01:16:17,004
Cold and miserable.
冷得慎人

875
01:16:18,609 --> 01:16:22,281
Just like Barney Balaban's face.
就像咱老板的脸

876
01:16:26,592 --> 01:16:28,848
Poor old Whit.
可怜的Whit啊

877
01:16:30,469 --> 01:16:34,336
He isn't worth a damn when he's not working with you.
他不跟你合作，一分钱不值！

878
01:16:39,394 --> 01:16:41,487
Neither am I.
我也是一样

879
01:16:47,724 --> 01:16:51,994
I couldn't pull off the picture this time.
我没法继续完成电影

880
01:16:52,018 --> 01:16:55,570
It just sits there,
它就在那儿

881
01:16:55,583 --> 01:16:58,192
refusing to come to life.
不愿意出来见人

882
01:17:02,323 --> 01:17:05,717
I guess there's no other way of saying it, is there?
我想也没有别的词形容了

883
01:17:08,011 --> 01:17:10,344
It's stillborn.
跟Whit的剧本一样

884
01:17:16,370 --> 01:17:19,028
I let you down, my love.
我让你失望了，亲爱的

885
01:17:24,124 --> 01:17:26,923
You deserve better.
你不该遭遇这些

886
01:17:34,271 --> 01:17:36,473
Better go feed Geoffrey and Stanley.
我该去喂喂大头们了

887
01:17:38,131 --> 01:17:40,400
Come on, boys.
大头来吃东西咯！

888
01:18:59,695 --> 01:19:02,705
I don't think I can stand us both being maudlin.
我还是觉得就一个人哭哭啼啼的就好了

889
01:19:03,798 --> 01:19:09,192
That tiresome little Hitchcock imitation I've been helping Whit finish is done.
那个模仿希区柯克风格的烂剧本我再也不帮忙了

890
01:19:12,750 --> 01:19:14,957
You know there's only one solution to all this.
你知道现在只有一条路

891
01:19:14,981 --> 01:19:17,458
That we get back to work together.
我们一起工作

892
01:19:18,472 --> 01:19:21,537
The fact is I rather like living in this house.
实话是，我还是想住在这间房子里

893
01:19:21,560 --> 01:19:25,430
So I suggest, for everyone's sake, we start whipping Psycho into shape.
所以我建议，对你我都好，我们开始搞好《惊魂记》

894
01:19:28,356 --> 01:19:30,706
You may not be the easiest man to live with,
你也许不是生活在一起最轻松的男人

895
01:19:30,717 --> 01:19:33,908
but you know how to cut a picture better than anyone else.
但是你比任何人都知道如何剪辑一部好电影

896
01:19:38,489 --> 01:19:40,852
Except for you.
除了你

897
01:19:43,244 --> 01:19:46,015
The second take. The light is much better on the hands.
第二个镜头手上的亮度要更好

898
01:19:50,089 --> 01:19:53,182
Only cut back to Janet once the car's already moving.
汽车发动了画面就停留在Janet上

899
01:19:53,194 --> 01:19:54,967
Cut it tighter.
节奏快点

900
01:19:58,159 --> 01:20:01,365
Ooh, you imp, you got nudity in there!
希胖你的坏蛋，你居然拍了裸体

901
01:20:01,388 --> 01:20:06,457
Her breasts were rather large. It was a challenge not to show them.
她胸部太大了，镜头躲不开

902
01:20:06,481 --> 01:20:08,221
You'll have to cut those six or seven frames
你必须得剪掉这六七格

903
01:20:08,232 --> 01:20:10,474
where she blinks after she's supposed to be dead.
她死了怎么可能还眨眼睛

904
01:20:10,492 --> 01:20:13,863
Alma, we've viewed the film a thousand times.
Alma，这部分我们看了好几遍

905
01:20:13,874 --> 01:20:15,671
She does not blink.
她没有眨眼睛

906
01:20:18,447 --> 01:20:21,888
- How's it going in there? - Swimmingly.
- 里面进展怎么样？ - 特别顺利

907
01:20:21,910 --> 01:20:24,145
Everyone's saying it's like a dog with fleas.
所有人都说这电影就像一只满是跳蚤的狗

908
01:20:25,177 --> 01:20:27,220
No, absolutely not!
不行，绝对不行

909
01:20:27,231 --> 01:20:30,449
I do not want music over the show murder scene.
我不想让谋杀戏有背景音乐

910
01:20:30,460 --> 01:20:32,820
But what Alma and I talked about is really going to play.
但是Alma和我已经商量好了应该要放

911
01:20:32,838 --> 01:20:36,324
Bernie, this is not Vertigo. It's not a romantic movie.
Bernie，这不是《迷魂记》，不是浪漫爱情电影

912
01:20:36,339 --> 01:20:38,121
The images must work on their own.
画面要让画面自己说话

913
01:20:38,144 --> 01:20:40,481
Yes, but you can't scare people just by going, "Boo!"
没错，但是光靠“咚”一声是吓不了观众的

914
01:20:40,492 --> 01:20:42,500
All right, you do it then. You know best.
好啊，有种你放啊，你最懂了

915
01:20:42,524 --> 01:20:44,212
- They have to anticipate it. - You always know best, just do it!
- 音乐必须参与叙事 - 你放啊，你放啊

916
01:20:44,235 --> 01:20:45,752
Take a step back.
你必须退一步

917
01:20:59,788 --> 01:21:04,037
- What do you think? - I think I'll never have a shower again.
- 你怎么想？ - 我觉得我再也不敢洗澡了

918
01:21:06,580 --> 01:21:09,571
- Hitch? - It's getting there.
- 希胖呢？ - 漂亮

919
01:21:13,496 --> 01:21:16,953
I distinctly saw both the stabbing and the nudity.
我清楚地看到了刀扎和裸露的画面

920
01:21:16,972 --> 01:21:21,658
What you think you're seeing is purely informed by the power of suggestion.
你以为你看到了，事实上不过是画面的暗示

921
01:21:21,673 --> 01:21:24,785
I assure you once you view the final version
我保证，当你看一遍最终版本

922
01:21:24,808 --> 01:21:27,110
with Mr. Herrmann's lovely, lyrical score...
配上Herrmann写的动听的旋律

923
01:21:27,133 --> 01:21:31,512
A lyrical score is not going to change my opinion.
动听的旋律是不会改变我的观点

924
01:21:32,698 --> 01:21:35,621
We're denying your seal.
我们不会允许你上映

925
01:21:36,526 --> 01:21:39,903
Geoffrey, would you mind if we had a word in private, please?
Geoffrey，让我们俩单独聊聊

926
01:21:46,411 --> 01:21:48,257
Thank you.
谢谢

927
01:21:54,455 --> 01:21:56,508
Now look here.
你听好

928
01:21:56,531 --> 01:21:59,666
I have a modest proposal to make.
我有一个最谨慎的建议

929
01:21:59,678 --> 01:22:03,013
If you're willing to leave the shower sequence as it is,
如果你同意保留洗澡的镜头

930
01:22:03,036 --> 01:22:08,415
I will re-shoot the opening love scene to your exact specifications.
我们会按照你的规格重新拍一遍开场的情爱戏

931
01:22:08,439 --> 01:22:13,718
In fact, I would welcome your personal supervision on the set.
我甚至还欢迎你到现场亲自监督

932
01:22:17,445 --> 01:22:19,558
To my specifications?
按照我的规格？

933
01:22:19,570 --> 01:22:22,376
But of course, my dear fellow.
不过当然了，我亲爱的你

934
01:22:22,400 --> 01:22:25,277
If only audiences could fully comprehend
只要观众们可以完全理解

935
01:22:25,301 --> 01:22:28,729
how tirelessly you work to help us entertain them
你是多么努力地去帮我们娱乐他们

936
01:22:28,753 --> 01:22:32,882
while protecting them from filth and indecency.
同时还要不让他们看到脏东西

937
01:22:39,646 --> 01:22:42,131
He's been harassing you since you announced this project,
从电影准备开始他就一直干扰你

938
01:22:42,154 --> 01:22:44,550
you invite him to the set, and he doesn't even show up?
你都邀请他来片场了，他还不来

939
01:22:44,573 --> 01:22:46,228
What did you tell him?
你怎么跟他说的啊

940
01:22:46,251 --> 01:22:49,119
That I respected him deeply.
我说我十分尊重他的工作

941
01:22:52,920 --> 01:22:58,181
Ladies and gentleman, that is a wrap. Thank you all very much.
杀青了各位，非常感谢大家

942
01:23:01,655 --> 01:23:05,107
- I thought we were re-shooting the scene. - The charade is over.
- 我以为我们要重新拍这一幕 - 不过是一个伪装

943
01:23:05,131 --> 01:23:06,907
Thank you.
谢谢你

944
01:23:12,926 --> 01:23:16,578
See, I wasn't that much of a monster to work with, was I?
我也不是不能合作的嘛？

945
01:23:16,601 --> 01:23:18,280
Not at all.
完全不会

946
01:23:18,304 --> 01:23:21,257
I hope I was sufficiently loyal to the cause.
我希望我没给这添什么麻烦

947
01:23:21,281 --> 01:23:24,183
Worthy of a Purple Heart, my dear.
你绝对值得一枚紫心徽章

948
