"the guards can help you deal with customers who run amok.
“保安可以帮助你搞定观众惊慌乱跑的情况

964
01:24:52,687 --> 01:24:54,588
"Post our special lobby clocks
“在大厅摆上我们的倒计时

965
01:24:54,612 --> 01:24:58,980
"to remind audiences of the starting times for Psycho.
“提醒观众《惊魂记》什么时候开始

966
01:24:59,003 --> 01:25:03,850
The manager of this fine motion picture theater has been advised
本电影院经理让各位

967
01:25:03,874 --> 01:25:08,955
not to allow anyone to enter the theater once Psycho begins.
在电影开演后保证不要让任何人进入放映厅

968
01:25:08,979 --> 01:25:13,608
Now, should you be so foolish as to attempt to slip in by a side entrance,
如此，如果有人还想从侧门、防火通道或是天窗

969
01:25:13,631 --> 01:25:16,434
a fire escape or through a skylight,
偷偷溜进来

970
01:25:16,458 --> 01:25:19,922
you will be ejected by brute force.
他们会被暴力驱逐

971
01:25:19,945 --> 01:25:22,383
More playful, darling.
语气有趣点好么

972
01:25:22,406 --> 01:25:28,336
"To further emphasize the sheer, unrelenting shock and suspense of Psycho,
“为了更好地强化电影中的跌宕剧情、憾人的惊吓和悬疑

973
01:25:28,359 --> 01:25:31,457
"right after the closing title "The End,"
“在电影”完“之后，

974
01:25:31,480 --> 01:25:39,794
"we strongly recommend that you close your house curtains over the screen for a full 30 seconds.
“我们强烈建议拉上银幕帘幕三十秒

975
01:25:40,908 --> 01:25:44,102
"By doing so, the horror of Psycho
“这样做，《惊魂记》的恐怖

976
01:25:44,125 --> 01:25:50,102
"will be indelibly etched in the mind and heart of your audience.
“将永远烙印在观众的脑子里

977
01:25:50,125 --> 01:25:54,924
Sincerely and emphatically, Alfred Hitchcock."
你最真诚而坚决的，阿弗莱德・希区柯克”

978
01:25:54,948 --> 01:25:57,247
Well at least there are some people here, Hitch.
起码还有点人来看，希胖

979
01:26:05,616 --> 01:26:07,536
We've roped off some seats for you.
我们为你们占了几个座

980
01:26:08,812 --> 01:26:10,754
- You go on ahead. - Are you sure?
- 你先去 - 你确定？

981
01:26:10,773 --> 01:26:13,473
Yes, I'll be with you in a moment. I'm just going to check the print. You go on.
我马上就上去。我去检查一下胶片。快去吧

982
01:26:13,497 --> 01:26:15,904
All right, darling. We'll save you a seat, all right?
那好，我们帮你占着座

983
01:26:17,336 --> 01:26:19,345
This way, Mr. Hitchcock.
这边，希胖

984
01:28:19,781 --> 01:28:21,584
Just got off the phone with Balaban.
刚跟老板通了电话

985
01:28:21,607 --> 01:28:25,181
He said congratulations. A well-deserved triumph, as we always knew.
他对你表示祝贺，正如大家所期望的，一次巨大的成功

986
01:28:25,200 --> 01:28:27,534
As we always knew, ha!
“正如大家所期望”是么，哈哈

987
01:28:27,557 --> 01:28:31,791
- Does this mean I can take the weekend off now? - Yes, dear. Thank you so much.
- 这是不是意味着我可以休息一个周末？ - 是的亲爱的。这段时间谢谢你

988
01:28:31,815 --> 01:28:34,105
- Where's Alma? - Go. Go on.
- Alma呢？ - 去吧去吧

989
01:28:45,566 --> 01:28:47,923
Alma, come here.
Alma，来

990
01:28:54,957 --> 01:28:58,581
You know, darling, this could be the biggest success of your career.
你知道，亲爱的，这或许是你事业中最大的成功

991
01:29:00,061 --> 01:29:02,597
Our career.
是我们的事业

992
01:29:04,143 --> 01:29:11,761
Alma, I will never be able to find a Hitchcock blonde as beautiful as you.
Alma，我永远找不到像你一样美丽的“希区柯克式金发女郎”

993
01:29:17,040 --> 01:29:20,858
